var book = {
	"name": "Numbers",
	"numChapters": 36,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3606A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3606A\"></sup>in the wilderness of Sinai, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3606B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3606B\"></sup>in the tent of meeting, on the first day of the second month, in the second year after they had come out of the land of Egypt, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3607C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3607C\"></sup>“Take a census of all the congregation of the people of Israel, by clans, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3607D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3607D\"></sup>by fathers' houses, according to the number of names, every male, head by head.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3608E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3608E\"></sup>From twenty years old and upward, all in Israel who are able to go to war, you and Aaron shall list them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3608F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3608F\"></sup>company by company.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And there shall be with you a man from each tribe, each man being the head of the house of his fathers.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And these are the names of the men who shall assist you. From Reuben, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3610G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3610G\"></sup>Elizur the son of Shedeur;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>from Simeon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3611H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3611H\"></sup>Shelumiel the son of Zurishaddai;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>from Judah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3612I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3612I\"></sup>Nahshon the son of Amminadab;",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>from Issachar, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3613J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3613J\"></sup>Nethanel the son of Zuar;",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>from Zebulun, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3614K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3614K\"></sup>Eliab the son of Helon;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>from the sons of Joseph, from Ephraim, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3615L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3615L\"></sup>Elishama the son of Ammihud, and from Manasseh, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3615M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3615M\"></sup>Gamaliel the son of Pedahzur;",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>from Benjamin, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3616N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3616N\"></sup>Abidan the son of Gideoni;",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>from Dan, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3617O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3617O\"></sup>Ahiezer the son of Ammishaddai;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>from Asher, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3618P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3618P\"></sup>Pagiel the son of Ochran;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>from Gad, Eliasaph the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3619Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3619Q\"></sup>Deuel;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>from Naphtali, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3620R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3620R\"></sup>Ahira the son of Enan.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>These were the ones <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3621S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3621S\"></sup>chosen from the congregation, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3621T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3621T\"></sup>the chiefs of their ancestral tribes, the heads of the clans of Israel.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Moses and Aaron took these men <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3622U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3622U\"></sup>who had been named,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and on the first day of the second month, they assembled the whole congregation together, who registered themselves by clans, by fathers' houses, according to the number of names from twenty years old and upward, head by head,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses. So he listed them in the wilderness of Sinai.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The people of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3625V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3625V\"></sup>Reuben, Israel's firstborn, their generations, by their clans, by their fathers' houses, according to the number of names, head by head, every male from twenty years old and upward, all who were able to go to war:",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>those listed of the tribe of Reuben were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3626W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3626W\"></sup>46,500.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Of the people of Simeon, their generations, by their clans, by their fathers' houses, those of them who were listed, according to the number of names, head by head, every male from twenty years old and upward, all who were able to go to war:",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>those listed of the tribe of Simeon were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3628X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3628X\"></sup>59,300.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Of the people of Gad, their generations, by their clans, by their fathers' houses, according to the number of the names, from twenty years old and upward, all who were able to go to war:",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>those listed of the tribe of Gad were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3630Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3630Y\"></sup>45,650.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Of the people of Judah, their generations, by their clans, by their fathers' houses, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and upward, every man able to go to war:",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>those listed of the tribe of Judah were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3632Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3632Z\"></sup>74,600.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Of the people of Issachar, their generations, by their clans, by their fathers' houses, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and upward, every man able to go to war:",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>those listed of the tribe of Issachar were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3634AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3634AA\"></sup>54,400.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Of the people of Zebulun, their generations, by their clans, by their fathers' houses, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and upward, every man able to go to war:",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>those listed of the tribe of Zebulun were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3636AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3636AB\"></sup>57,400.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Of the people of Joseph, namely, of the people of Ephraim, their generations, by their clans, by their fathers' houses, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and upward, every man able to go to war:",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>those listed of the tribe of Ephraim were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3638AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3638AC\"></sup>40,500.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Of the people of Manasseh, their generations, by their clans, by their fathers' houses, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and upward, every man able to go to war:",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>those listed of the tribe of Manasseh were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3640AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3640AD\"></sup>32,200.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Of the people of Benjamin, their generations, by their clans, by their fathers' houses, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and upward, every man able to go to war:",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>those listed of the tribe of Benjamin were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3642AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3642AE\"></sup>35,400.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Of the people of Dan, their generations, by their clans, by their fathers' houses, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and upward, every man able to go to war:",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>those listed of the tribe of Dan were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3644AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3644AF\"></sup>62,700.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Of the people of Asher, their generations, by their clans, by their fathers' houses, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and upward, every man able to go to war:",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>those listed of the tribe of Asher were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3646AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3646AG\"></sup>41,500.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Of the people of Naphtali, their generations, by their clans, by their fathers' houses, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and upward, every man able to go to war:",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>those listed of the tribe of Naphtali were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3648AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3648AH\"></sup>53,400.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3649AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3649AI\"></sup>These are those who were listed, whom Moses and Aaron listed with the help of the chiefs of Israel, twelve men, each representing his fathers' house.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>So all those listed of the people of Israel, by their fathers' houses, from twenty years old and upward, every man able to go to war in Israel—",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>all those listed were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3651AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3651AJ\"></sup>603,550.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3652AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3652AK\"></sup>the Levites were not listed along with them by their ancestral tribe.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>“Only the tribe of Levi you shall not list, and you shall not take a census of them among the people of Israel.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3655AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3655AL\"></sup>But appoint the Levites over the tabernacle of the testimony, and over all its furnishings, and over all that belongs to it. They are to carry the tabernacle and all its furnishings, and they shall take care of it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3655AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3655AM\"></sup>and shall camp around the tabernacle.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3656AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3656AN\"></sup>When the tabernacle is to set out, the Levites shall take it down, and when the tabernacle is to be pitched, the Levites shall set it up. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3656AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3656AO\"></sup>And if any outsider comes near, he shall be put to death.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>The people of Israel shall pitch their tents by their companies, each man in his own camp and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3657AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3657AP\"></sup>each man by his own standard.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>But the Levites shall camp around the tabernacle of the testimony, so that there may be no <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3658AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3658AQ\"></sup>wrath on the congregation of the people of Israel. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3658AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3658AR\"></sup>And the Levites shall keep guard over the tabernacle of the testimony.”",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>Thus did the people of Israel; they did according to all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses and Aaron, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3661A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3661A\"></sup>“The people of Israel shall camp each by his own standard, with the banners of their fathers' houses. They shall camp facing the tent of meeting on every side.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Those to camp on the east side toward the sunrise shall be of the standard of the camp of Judah by their companies, the chief of the people of Judah being <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3662B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3662B\"></sup>Nahshon the son of Amminadab,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>his company as listed being 74,600.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Those to camp next to him shall be the tribe of Issachar, the chief of the people of Issachar being Nethanel the son of Zuar,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>his company as listed being 54,400.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then the tribe of Zebulun, the chief of the people of Zebulun being Eliab the son of Helon,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>his company as listed being 57,400.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>All those listed of the camp of Judah, by their companies, were 186,400. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3668C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3668C\"></sup>They shall set out first on the march.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“On the south side shall be the standard of the camp of Reuben by their companies, the chief of the people of Reuben being Elizur the son of Shedeur,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>his company as listed being 46,500.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And those to camp next to him shall be the tribe of Simeon, the chief of the people of Simeon being Shelumiel the son of Zurishaddai,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>his company as listed being 59,300.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then the tribe of Gad, the chief of the people of Gad being Eliasaph the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3673D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3673D\"></sup>Reuel,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>his company as listed being 45,650.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>All those listed of the camp of Reuben, by their companies, were 151,450. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3675E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3675E\"></sup>They shall set out second.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3676F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3676F\"></sup>“Then the tent of meeting shall set out, with the camp of the Levites in the midst of the camps; as they camp, so shall they set out, each in position, standard by standard.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“On the west side shall be the standard of the camp of Ephraim by their companies, the chief of the people of Ephraim being Elishama the son of Ammihud,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>his company as listed being 40,500.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And next to him shall be the tribe of Manasseh, the chief of the people of Manasseh being Gamaliel the son of Pedahzur,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>his company as listed being 32,200.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then the tribe of Benjamin, the chief of the people of Benjamin being Abidan the son of Gideoni,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>his company as listed being 35,400.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>All those listed of the camp of Ephraim, by their companies, were 108,100. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3683G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3683G\"></sup>They shall set out third on the march.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“On the north side shall be the standard of the camp of Dan by their companies, the chief of the people of Dan being Ahiezer the son of Ammishaddai,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>his company as listed being 62,700.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And those to camp next to him shall be the tribe of Asher, the chief of the people of Asher being Pagiel the son of Ochran,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>his company as listed being 41,500.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then the tribe of Naphtali, the chief of the people of Naphtali being Ahira the son of Enan,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>his company as listed being 53,400.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>All those listed of the camp of Dan were 157,600. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3690H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3690H\"></sup>They shall set out last, standard by standard.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>These are the people of Israel as listed by their fathers' houses. All those listed in the camps by their companies were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3691I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3691I\"></sup>603,550.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3692J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3692J\"></sup>the Levites were not listed among the people of Israel, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Thus did the people of Israel. According to all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3693K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3693K\"></sup>so they camped by their standards, and so they set out, each one in his clan, according to his fathers' house."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>These are the generations of Aaron and Moses at the time when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke with Moses on Mount Sinai.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>These are the names of the sons of Aaron: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3695A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3695A\"></sup>Nadab the firstborn, and Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>These are the names of the sons of Aaron, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3696B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3696B\"></sup>the anointed priests, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3696C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3696C\"></sup>whom he ordained to serve as priests.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3697D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3697D\"></sup>But Nadab and Abihu died before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> when they offered unauthorized fire before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the wilderness of Sinai, and they had no children. So Eleazar and Ithamar served as priests in the lifetime of Aaron their father.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3699E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3699E\"></sup>“Bring the tribe of Levi near, and set them before Aaron the priest, that they may minister to him.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They shall keep guard over him and over the whole congregation before the tent of meeting, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3700F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3700F\"></sup>as they minister at the tabernacle.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They shall guard all the furnishings of the tent of meeting, and keep guard over the people of Israel as they minister at the tabernacle.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3702G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3702G\"></sup>you shall give the Levites to Aaron and his sons; they are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3702H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3702H\"></sup>wholly given to him from among the people of Israel.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And you shall appoint Aaron and his sons, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3703I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3703I\"></sup>they shall guard their priesthood. But if <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3703J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3703J\"></sup>any outsider comes near, he shall be put to death.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3705K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3705K\"></sup>I have taken the Levites from among the people of Israel instead of every firstborn who opens the womb among the people of Israel. The Levites shall be mine,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3706L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3706L\"></sup>all the firstborn are mine. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3706M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3706M\"></sup>On the day that I struck down all the firstborn in the land of Egypt, I consecrated for my own all the firstborn in Israel, both of man and of beast. They shall be mine: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses in the wilderness of Sinai, saying,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“List the sons of Levi, by fathers' houses and by clans; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3708N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3708N\"></sup>every male from a month old and upward you shall list.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So Moses listed them according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as he was commanded.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3710O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3710O\"></sup>And these were the sons of Levi by their names: Gershon and Kohath and Merari.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And these are the names of the sons of Gershon by their clans: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3711P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3711P\"></sup>Libni and Shimei.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And the sons of Kohath by their clans: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3712Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3712Q\"></sup>Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And the sons of Merari by their clans: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3713R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3713R\"></sup>Mahli and Mushi. These are the clans of the Levites, by their fathers' houses.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>To Gershon belonged the clan of the Libnites and the clan of the Shimeites; these were the clans of the Gershonites.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Their listing according to the number of all the males from a month old and upward was 7,500.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3716S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3716S\"></sup>The clans of the Gershonites were to camp behind the tabernacle on the west,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>with Eliasaph, the son of Lael as chief of the fathers' house of the Gershonites.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3718T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3718T\"></sup>guard duty of the sons of Gershon in the tent of meeting involved <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3718U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3718U\"></sup>the tabernacle, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3718V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3718V\"></sup>the tent with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3718W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3718W\"></sup>its covering, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3718X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3718X\"></sup>the screen for the entrance of the tent of meeting,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3719Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3719Y\"></sup>the hangings of the court, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3719Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3719Z\"></sup>the screen for the door of the court that is around the tabernacle and the altar, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3719AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3719AA\"></sup>its cords—all the service connected with these.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>To Kohath belonged the clan of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3720AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3720AB\"></sup>Amramites and the clan of the Izharites and the clan of the Hebronites and the clan of the Uzzielites; these are the clans of the Kohathites.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>According to the number of all the males, from a month old and upward, there were 8,600, keeping guard over the sanctuary.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The clans of the sons of Kohath were to camp on the south side of the tabernacle,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3723AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3723AC\"></sup>Elizaphan the son of Uzziel as chief of the fathers' house of the clans of the Kohathites.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And their guard duty involved <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3724AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3724AD\"></sup>the ark, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3724AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3724AE\"></sup>the table, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3724AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3724AF\"></sup>the lampstand, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3724AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3724AG\"></sup>the altars, the vessels of the sanctuary with which the priests minister, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3724AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3724AH\"></sup>the screen; all the service connected with these.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And Eleazar the son of Aaron the priest was to be chief over the chiefs of the Levites, and to have oversight of those who kept guard over the sanctuary.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>To Merari belonged the clan of the Mahlites and the clan of the Mushites: these are the clans of Merari.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Their listing according to the number of all the males from a month old and upward was 6,200.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And the chief of the fathers' house of the clans of Merari was Zuriel the son of Abihail. They were to camp on the north side of the tabernacle.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3729AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3729AI\"></sup>And the appointed guard duty of the sons of Merari involved the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3729AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3729AJ\"></sup>frames of the tabernacle, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3729AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3729AK\"></sup>the bars, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3729AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3729AL\"></sup>the pillars, the bases, and all their accessories; all the service connected with these;",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3730AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3730AM\"></sup>the pillars around the court, with their bases and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3730AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3730AN\"></sup>pegs and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3730AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3730AO\"></sup>cords.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Those who were to camp before the tabernacle on the east, before the tent of meeting toward the sunrise, were Moses and Aaron and his sons, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3731AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3731AP\"></sup>guarding the sanctuary itself, to protect the people of Israel. And any outsider who came near was to be put to death.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>All those listed among the Levites, whom Moses and Aaron listed at the commandment of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, by clans, all the males from a month old and upward, were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3732AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3732AQ\"></sup>22,000.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “List all the firstborn males of the people of Israel, from a month old and upward, taking the number of their names.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3734AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3734AR\"></sup>And you shall take the Levites for me—I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—instead of all the firstborn among the people of Israel, and the cattle of the Levites instead of all the firstborn among the cattle of the people of Israel.”",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>So Moses listed all the firstborn among the people of Israel, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded him.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>And all the firstborn males, according to the number of names, from a month old and upward as listed were 22,273.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3738AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3738AS\"></sup>“Take the Levites instead of all the firstborn among the people of Israel, and the cattle of the Levites instead of their cattle. The Levites shall be mine: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3739AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3739AT\"></sup>as the redemption price for the 273 of the firstborn of the people of Israel, over and above the number of the male Levites,",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>you shall take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3740AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3740AU\"></sup>five shekels per head; you shall take them according to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3740AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3740AV\"></sup>the shekel of the sanctuary (the shekel of twenty gerahs),",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>and give the money to Aaron and his sons as the redemption price for those who are over.”",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>So Moses took the redemption money from those who were over and above those redeemed by the Levites.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>From the firstborn of the people of Israel he took the money, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3743AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3743AW\"></sup>1,365 shekels, by the shekel of the sanctuary.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>And Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3744AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3744AX\"></sup>gave the redemption money to Aaron and his sons, according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses and Aaron, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Take a census of the sons of Kohath from among the sons of Levi, by their clans and their fathers' houses,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3747A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3747A\"></sup>from thirty years old up to fifty years old, all who can come on duty, to do the work in the tent of meeting.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>This is the service of the sons of Kohath in the tent of meeting: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3748B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3748B\"></sup>the most holy things.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When the camp is to set out, Aaron and his sons shall go in and take down <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3749C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3749C\"></sup>the veil of the screen and cover <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3749D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3749D\"></sup>the ark of the testimony with it.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then they shall put on it a covering of goatskin and spread on top of that a cloth all of blue, and shall put in its <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3750E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3750E\"></sup>poles.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And over the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3751F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3751F\"></sup>table of the bread of the Presence they shall spread a cloth of blue and put on it the plates, the dishes for incense, the bowls, and the flagons for the drink offering; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3751G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3751G\"></sup>the regular showbread also shall be on it.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then they shall spread over them a cloth of scarlet and cover the same with a covering of goatskin, and shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3752H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3752H\"></sup>put in its poles.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And they shall take a cloth of blue and cover <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3753I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3753I\"></sup>the lampstand for the light, with its lamps, its tongs, its trays, and all the vessels for oil with which it is supplied.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And they shall put it with all its utensils in a covering of goatskin and put it on the carrying frame.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And over <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3755J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3755J\"></sup>the golden altar they shall spread a cloth of blue and cover it with a covering of goatskin, and shall put in its poles.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And they shall take all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3756K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3756K\"></sup>the vessels of the service that are used in the sanctuary and put them in a cloth of blue and cover them with a covering of goatskin and put them on the carrying frame.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And they shall take away the ashes from the altar and spread a purple cloth over it.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And they shall put on it all the utensils of the altar, which are used for the service there, the fire pans, the forks, the shovels, and the basins, all the utensils of the altar; and they shall spread on it a covering of goatskin, and shall put in its poles.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And when Aaron and his sons have finished covering the sanctuary and all the furnishings of the sanctuary, as the camp sets out, after that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3759L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3759L\"></sup>the sons of Kohath shall come to carry these, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3759M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3759M\"></sup>but they must not touch the holy things, lest they die. These are the things of the tent of meeting that the sons of Kohath are to carry.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“And Eleazar the son of Aaron the priest shall have charge of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3760N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3760N\"></sup>the oil for the light, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3760O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3760O\"></sup>fragrant incense, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3760P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3760P\"></sup>the regular grain offering, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3760Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3760Q\"></sup>the anointing oil, with the oversight of the whole tabernacle and all that is in it, of the sanctuary and its vessels.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses and Aaron, saying,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“Let not the tribe of the clans of the Kohathites be destroyed from among the Levites,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>but deal thus with them, that they may live and not die when they come near to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3763R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3763R\"></sup>the most holy things: Aaron and his sons shall go in and appoint them each to his task and to his burden,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3764S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3764S\"></sup>but they shall not go in to look on the holy things even for a moment, lest they die.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“Take a census of the sons of Gershon also, by their fathers' houses and by their clans.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3767T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3767T\"></sup>From thirty years old up to fifty years old, you shall list them, all who can <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3767U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3767U\"></sup>come to do duty, to do service in the tent of meeting.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>This is the service of the clans of the Gershonites, in serving and bearing burdens:",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3769V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3769V\"></sup>they shall carry <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3769W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3769W\"></sup>the curtains of the tabernacle and the tent of meeting with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3769X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3769X\"></sup>its covering and the covering of goatskin that is on top of it and the screen for the entrance of the tent of meeting",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>and the hangings of the court and the screen for the entrance of the gate of the court that is around the tabernacle and the altar, and their cords and all the equipment for their service. And they shall do all that needs to be done with regard to them.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>All the service of the sons of the Gershonites shall be at the command of Aaron and his sons, in all that they are to carry and in all that they have to do. And you shall assign to their charge all that they are to carry.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>This is the service of the clans of the sons of the Gershonites in the tent of meeting, and their guard duty is to be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3772Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3772Y\"></sup>under the direction of Ithamar the son of Aaron the priest.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“As for the sons of Merari, you shall list them by their clans and their fathers' houses.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3774Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3774Z\"></sup>From thirty years old up to fifty years old, you shall list them, everyone who can come on duty, to do the service of the tent of meeting.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3775AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3775AA\"></sup>this is what they are charged to carry, as the whole of their service in the tent of meeting: the frames of the tabernacle, with its bars, pillars, and bases,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>and the pillars around the court with their bases, pegs, and cords, with all their equipment and all their accessories. And you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3776AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3776AB\"></sup>list by name the objects that they are required to carry.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>This is the service of the clans of the sons of Merari, the whole of their service in the tent of meeting, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3777AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3777AC\"></sup>under the direction of Ithamar the son of Aaron the priest.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And Moses and Aaron and the chiefs of the congregation listed the sons of the Kohathites, by their clans and their fathers' houses,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3779AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3779AD\"></sup>from thirty years old up to fifty years old, everyone who could come on duty, for service in the tent of meeting;",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>and those listed by clans were 2,750.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3781AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3781AE\"></sup>This was the list of the clans of the Kohathites, all who served in the tent of meeting, whom Moses and Aaron listed according to the commandment of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by Moses.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Those listed of the sons of Gershon, by their clans and their fathers' houses,",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3783AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3783AF\"></sup>from thirty years old up to fifty years old, everyone who could come on duty for service in the tent of meeting—",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>those listed by their clans and their fathers' houses were 2,630.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3785AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3785AG\"></sup>This was the list of the clans of the sons of Gershon, all who served in the tent of meeting, whom Moses and Aaron listed according to the commandment of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Those listed of the clans of the sons of Merari, by their clans and their fathers' houses,",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3787AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3787AH\"></sup>from thirty years old up to fifty years old, everyone who could come on duty, for service in the tent of meeting—",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>those listed by clans were 3,200.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3789AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3789AI\"></sup>This was the list of the clans of the sons of Merari, whom Moses and Aaron listed according to the commandment of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by Moses.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>All those who were listed of the Levites, whom Moses and Aaron and the chiefs of Israel listed, by their clans and their fathers' houses,",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3791AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3791AJ\"></sup>from thirty years old up to fifty years old, everyone who could come to do the service of ministry and the service of bearing burdens in the tent of meeting,",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>those listed were 8,580.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>According to the commandment of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> through Moses they were listed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3793AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3793AK\"></sup>each one with his task of serving or carrying. Thus they were listed by him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3793AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3793AL\"></sup>as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Command the people of Israel that they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3795A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3795A\"></sup>put out of the camp everyone who is leprous or has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3795B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3795B\"></sup>a discharge and everyone who is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3795C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3795C\"></sup>unclean through contact with the dead.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You shall put out both male and female, putting them outside the camp, that they may not defile their camp, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3796D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3796D\"></sup>in the midst of which I dwell.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And the people of Israel did so, and put them outside the camp; as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, so the people of Israel did.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“Speak to the people of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3799E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3799E\"></sup>When a man or woman commits any of the sins that people commit by breaking faith with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and that person realizes his guilt,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3800F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3800F\"></sup>he shall confess his sin that he has committed. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3800G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3800G\"></sup>And he shall make full restitution for his wrong, adding a fifth to it and giving it to him to whom he did the wrong.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But if the man has no next of kin to whom restitution may be made for the wrong, the restitution for wrong shall go to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for the priest, in addition to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3801H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3801H\"></sup>the ram of atonement with which atonement is made for him.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3802I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3802I\"></sup>every contribution, all the holy donations of the people of Israel, which they bring to the priest, shall be his.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Each one shall keep his holy donations: whatever anyone gives to the priest shall be his.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“Speak to the people of Israel, If any man's wife goes astray and breaks faith with him,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>if a man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3806J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3806J\"></sup>lies with her sexually, and it is hidden from the eyes of her husband, and she is undetected though she has defiled herself, and there is no witness against her, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3806K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3806K\"></sup>since she was not taken in the act,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and if the spirit of jealousy comes over him and he is jealous of his wife who has defiled herself, or if the spirit of jealousy comes over him and he is jealous of his wife, though she has not defiled herself,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>then the man shall bring his wife to the priest and bring the offering required of her, a tenth of an ephah of barley flour. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3808L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3808L\"></sup>He shall pour no oil on it and put no frankincense on it, for it is a grain offering of jealousy, a grain offering of remembrance, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3808M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3808M\"></sup>bringing iniquity to remembrance.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“And the priest shall bring her near and set her before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And the priest shall take holy water in an earthenware vessel and take some of the dust that is on the floor of the tabernacle and put it into the water.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And the priest shall set the woman before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3811N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3811N\"></sup>unbind the hair of the woman's head and place in her hands the grain offering of remembrance, which is the grain offering of jealousy. And in his hand the priest shall have the water of bitterness that brings the curse.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then the priest shall make her take an oath, saying, ‘If no man has lain with you, and if you have not turned aside to uncleanness while you were under your husband's authority, be free from this water of bitterness that brings the curse.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But if you have gone astray, though you are under your husband's authority, and if you have defiled yourself, and some man other than your husband has lain with you,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>then’ (let the priest make the woman take the oath of the curse, and say to the woman) <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3814O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3814O\"></sup>‘the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> make you a curse and an oath among your people, when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> makes your thigh fall away and your body swell.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>May this water that brings the curse <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3815P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3815P\"></sup>pass into your bowels and make your womb swell and your thigh fall away.’ And the woman shall say, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3815Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3815Q\"></sup>‘Amen, Amen.’",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Then the priest shall write these curses in a book and wash them off into the water of bitterness.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And he shall make the woman drink the water of bitterness that brings the curse, and the water that brings the curse shall enter into her and cause bitter pain.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And the priest shall take the grain offering of jealousy out of the woman's hand <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3818R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3818R\"></sup>and shall wave the grain offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and bring it to the altar.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And the priest <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3819S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3819S\"></sup>shall take a handful of the grain offering, as its memorial portion, and burn it on the altar, and afterward shall make the woman drink the water.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And when he has made her drink the water, then, if she has defiled herself and has broken faith with her husband, the water that brings the curse shall enter into her and cause bitter pain, and her womb shall swell, and her thigh shall fall away, and the woman <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3820T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3820T\"></sup>shall become a curse among her people.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>But if the woman has not defiled herself and is clean, then she shall be free and shall conceive children.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“This is the law in cases of jealousy, when a wife, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3822U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3822U\"></sup>though under her husband's authority, goes astray and defiles herself,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>or when the spirit of jealousy comes over a man and he is jealous of his wife. Then he shall set the woman before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the priest shall carry out for her all this law.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The man shall be free from iniquity, but the woman <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3824V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3824V\"></sup>shall bear her iniquity.”"
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to the people of Israel and say to them, When either a man or a woman makes a special vow, the vow of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3826A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3826A\"></sup>a Nazirite, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3826B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3826B\"></sup>to separate himself to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3827C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3827C\"></sup>shall separate himself from wine and strong drink. He shall drink no vinegar made from wine or strong drink and shall not drink any juice of grapes or eat grapes, fresh or dried.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>All the days of his separation he shall eat nothing that is produced by the grapevine, not even the seeds or the skins.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“All the days of his vow of separation, no <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3829D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3829D\"></sup>razor shall touch his head. Until the time is completed for which he separates himself to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, he shall be holy. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3829E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3829E\"></sup>He shall let the locks of hair of his head grow long.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“All the days that he separates himself to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3830F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3830F\"></sup>he shall not go near a dead body.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3831G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3831G\"></sup>Not even for his father or for his mother, for brother or sister, if they die, shall he make himself unclean, because his separation to God is on his head.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>All the days of his separation he is holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“And if any man dies very suddenly beside him and he defiles his consecrated head, then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3833H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3833H\"></sup>he shall shave his head on the day of his cleansing; on the seventh day he shall shave it.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3834I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3834I\"></sup>On the eighth day he shall bring two turtledoves or two pigeons to the priest to the entrance of the tent of meeting,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and the priest shall offer one for a sin offering and the other for a burnt offering, and make atonement for him, because he sinned by reason of the dead body. And he shall consecrate his head that same day",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and separate himself to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for the days of his separation and bring a male lamb a year old <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3836J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3836J\"></sup>for a guilt offering. But the previous period shall be void, because his separation was defiled.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“And this is the law for the Nazirite, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3837K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3837K\"></sup>when the time of his separation has been completed: he shall be brought to the entrance of the tent of meeting,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and he shall bring his gift to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, one male lamb a year old without blemish for a burnt offering, and one ewe lamb a year old without blemish <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3838L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3838L\"></sup>as a sin offering, and one ram without blemish <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3838M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3838M\"></sup>as a peace offering,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and a basket of unleavened bread, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3839N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3839N\"></sup>loaves of fine flour mixed with oil, and unleavened wafers smeared with oil, and their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3839O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3839O\"></sup>grain offering and their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3839P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3839P\"></sup>drink offerings.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And the priest shall bring them before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and offer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3840Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3840Q\"></sup>his sin offering and his burnt offering,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and he shall offer the ram as a sacrifice of peace offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, with the basket of unleavened bread. The priest shall offer also its grain offering and its drink offering.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And the Nazirite <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3842R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3842R\"></sup>shall shave his consecrated head at the entrance of the tent of meeting and shall take the hair from his consecrated head and put it on the fire that is under the sacrifice of the peace offering.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And the priest shall take the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3843S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3843S\"></sup>shoulder of the ram, when it is boiled, and one unleavened loaf out of the basket and one unleavened wafer, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3843T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3843T\"></sup>shall put them on the hands of the Nazirite, after he has shaved the hair of his consecration,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and the priest shall wave them for a wave offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3844U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3844U\"></sup>They are a holy portion for the priest, together with the breast that is waved and the thigh that is contributed. And after that the Nazirite may drink wine.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“This is the law of the Nazirite. But if he vows an offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> above his Nazirite vow, as he can afford, in exact accordance with the vow that he takes, then he shall do in addition to the law of the Nazirite.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Speak to Aaron and his sons, saying, Thus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3847V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3847V\"></sup>you shall bless the people of Israel: you shall say to them,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3848W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3848W\"></sup>bless you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3848X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3848X\"></sup>keep you;",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3849Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3849Y\"></sup>make his face to shine upon you and be gracious to you;",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3850Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3850Z\"></sup>lift up his countenance upon you and give you peace.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3851AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3851AA\"></sup>“So shall they put my name upon the people of Israel, and I will bless them.”"
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>On the day when Moses had finished <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3852A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3852A\"></sup>setting up the tabernacle and had anointed and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3852B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3852B\"></sup>consecrated it with all its furnishings and had anointed and consecrated the altar with all its utensils,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3853C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3853C\"></sup>the chiefs of Israel, heads of their fathers' houses, who were the chiefs of the tribes, who were over those who were listed, approached",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and brought their offerings before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, six wagons and twelve oxen, a wagon for every two of the chiefs, and for each one an ox. They brought them before the tabernacle.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“Accept these from them, that they may be used in the service of the tent of meeting, and give them to the Levites, to each man according to his service.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Moses took the wagons and the oxen and gave them to the Levites.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Two wagons and four oxen <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3858D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3858D\"></sup>he gave to the sons of Gershon, according to their service.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And four wagons and eight oxen <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3859E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3859E\"></sup>he gave to the sons of Merari, according to their service, under the direction of Ithamar the son of Aaron the priest.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But to the sons of Kohath he gave none, because they were charged with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3860F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3860F\"></sup>the service of the holy things that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3860G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3860G\"></sup>had to be carried on the shoulder.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And the chiefs offered offerings for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3861H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3861H\"></sup>dedication of the altar on the day it was anointed; and the chiefs offered their offering before the altar.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “They shall offer their offerings, one chief each day, for the dedication of the altar.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He who offered his offering the first day was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3863I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3863I\"></sup>Nahshon the son of Amminadab, of the tribe of Judah.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And his offering was one silver plate whose weight was 130 shekels, one silver basin of 70 shekels, according to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3864J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3864J\"></sup>the shekel of the sanctuary, both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil for a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3864K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3864K\"></sup>grain offering;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>one golden dish of 10 shekels, full of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3865L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3865L\"></sup>incense;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3866M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3866M\"></sup>one bull from the herd, one ram, one male lamb a year old, for a burnt offering;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>one male goat for a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3867N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3867N\"></sup>sin offering;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3868O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3868O\"></sup>the sacrifice of peace offerings, two oxen, five rams, five male goats, and five male lambs a year old. This was the offering of Nahshon the son of Amminadab.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>On the second day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3869P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3869P\"></sup>Nethanel the son of Zuar, the chief of Issachar, made an offering.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He offered for his offering one silver plate whose weight was 130 shekels, one silver basin of 70 shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary, both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil for a grain offering;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>one golden dish of 10 shekels, full of incense;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>one bull from the herd, one ram, one male lamb a year old, for a burnt offering;",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>one male goat for a sin offering;",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>and for the sacrifice of peace offerings, two oxen, five rams, five male goats, and five male lambs a year old. This was the offering of Nethanel the son of Zuar.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>On the third day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3875Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3875Q\"></sup>Eliab the son of Helon, the chief of the people of Zebulun:",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>his offering was one silver plate whose weight was 130 shekels, one silver basin of 70 shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary, both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil for a grain offering;",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>one golden dish of 10 shekels, full of incense;",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>one bull from the herd, one ram, one male lamb a year old, for a burnt offering;",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>one male goat for a sin offering;",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>and for the sacrifice of peace offerings, two oxen, five rams, five male goats, and five male lambs a year old. This was the offering of Eliab the son of Helon.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>On the fourth day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3881R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3881R\"></sup>Elizur the son of Shedeur, the chief of the people of Reuben:",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>his offering was one silver plate whose weight was 130 shekels, one silver basin of 70 shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary, both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil for a grain offering;",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>one golden dish of 10 shekels, full of incense;",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>one bull from the herd, one ram, one male lamb a year old, for a burnt offering;",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>one male goat for a sin offering;",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>and for the sacrifice of peace offerings, two oxen, five rams, five male goats, and five male lambs a year old. This was the offering of Elizur the son of Shedeur.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>On the fifth day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3887S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3887S\"></sup>Shelumiel the son of Zurishaddai, the chief of the people of Simeon:",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>his offering was one silver plate whose weight was 130 shekels, one silver basin of 70 shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary, both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil for a grain offering;",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>one golden dish of 10 shekels, full of incense;",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>one bull from the herd, one ram, one male lamb a year old, for a burnt offering;",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>one male goat for a sin offering;",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>and for the sacrifice of peace offerings, two oxen, five rams, five male goats, and five male lambs a year old. This was the offering of Shelumiel the son of Zurishaddai.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>On the sixth day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3893T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3893T\"></sup>Eliasaph the son of Deuel, the chief of the people of Gad:",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>his offering was one silver plate whose weight was 130 shekels, one silver basin of 70 shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary, both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil for a grain offering;",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>one golden dish of 10 shekels, full of incense;",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>one bull from the herd, one ram, one male lamb a year old, for a burnt offering;",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>one male goat for a sin offering;",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>and for the sacrifice of peace offerings, two oxen, five rams, five male goats, and five male lambs a year old. This was the offering of Eliasaph the son of Deuel.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>On the seventh day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3899U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3899U\"></sup>Elishama the son of Ammihud, the chief of the people of Ephraim:",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>his offering was one silver plate whose weight was 130 shekels, one silver basin of 70 shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary, both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil for a grain offering;",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>one golden dish of 10 shekels, full of incense;",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>one bull from the herd, one ram, one male lamb a year old, for a burnt offering;",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>one male goat for a sin offering;",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>and for the sacrifice of peace offerings, two oxen, five rams, five male goats, and five male lambs a year old. This was the offering of Elishama the son of Ammihud.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>On the eighth day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3905V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3905V\"></sup>Gamaliel the son of Pedahzur, the chief of the people of Manasseh:",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>his offering was one silver plate whose weight was 130 shekels, one silver basin of 70 shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary, both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil for a grain offering;",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>one golden dish of 10 shekels, full of incense;",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>one bull from the herd, one ram, one male lamb a year old, for a burnt offering;",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>one male goat for a sin offering;",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>and for the sacrifice of peace offerings, two oxen, five rams, five male goats, and five male lambs a year old. This was the offering of Gamaliel the son of Pedahzur.",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup>On the ninth day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3911W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3911W\"></sup>Abidan the son of Gideoni, the chief of the people of Benjamin:",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup>his offering was one silver plate whose weight was 130 shekels, one silver basin of 70 shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary, both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil for a grain offering;",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup>one golden dish of 10 shekels, full of incense;",
			"63": "<sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup>one bull from the herd, one ram, one male lamb a year old, for a burnt offering;",
			"64": "<sup class=\"versenum\">64 </sup>one male goat for a sin offering;",
			"65": "<sup class=\"versenum\">65 </sup>and for the sacrifice of peace offerings, two oxen, five rams, five male goats, and five male lambs a year old. This was the offering of Abidan the son of Gideoni.",
			"66": "<sup class=\"versenum\">66 </sup>On the tenth day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3917X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3917X\"></sup>Ahiezer the son of Ammishaddai, the chief of the people of Dan:",
			"67": "<sup class=\"versenum\">67 </sup>his offering was one silver plate whose weight was 130 shekels, one silver basin of 70 shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary, both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil for a grain offering;",
			"68": "<sup class=\"versenum\">68 </sup>one golden dish of 10 shekels, full of incense;",
			"69": "<sup class=\"versenum\">69 </sup>one bull from the herd, one ram, one male lamb a year old, for a burnt offering;",
			"70": "<sup class=\"versenum\">70 </sup>one male goat for a sin offering;",
			"71": "<sup class=\"versenum\">71 </sup>and for the sacrifice of peace offerings, two oxen, five rams, five male goats, and five male lambs a year old. This was the offering of Ahiezer the son of Ammishaddai.",
			"72": "<sup class=\"versenum\">72 </sup>On the eleventh day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3923Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3923Y\"></sup>Pagiel the son of Ochran, the chief of the people of Asher:",
			"73": "<sup class=\"versenum\">73 </sup>his offering was one silver plate whose weight was 130 shekels, one silver basin of 70 shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary, both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil for a grain offering;",
			"74": "<sup class=\"versenum\">74 </sup>one golden dish of 10 shekels, full of incense;",
			"75": "<sup class=\"versenum\">75 </sup>one bull from the herd, one ram, one male lamb a year old, for a burnt offering;",
			"76": "<sup class=\"versenum\">76 </sup>one male goat for a sin offering;",
			"77": "<sup class=\"versenum\">77 </sup>and for the sacrifice of peace offerings, two oxen, five rams, five male goats, and five male lambs a year old. This was the offering of Pagiel the son of Ochran.",
			"78": "<sup class=\"versenum\">78 </sup>On the twelfth day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3929Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3929Z\"></sup>Ahira the son of Enan, the chief of the people of Naphtali:",
			"79": "<sup class=\"versenum\">79 </sup>his offering was one silver plate whose weight was 130 shekels, one silver basin of 70 shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary, both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil for a grain offering;",
			"80": "<sup class=\"versenum\">80 </sup>one golden dish of 10 shekels, full of incense;",
			"81": "<sup class=\"versenum\">81 </sup>one bull from the herd, one ram, one male lamb a year old, for a burnt offering;",
			"82": "<sup class=\"versenum\">82 </sup>one male goat for a sin offering;",
			"83": "<sup class=\"versenum\">83 </sup>and for the sacrifice of peace offerings, two oxen, five rams, five male goats, and five male lambs a year old. This was the offering of Ahira the son of Enan.",
			"84": "<sup class=\"versenum\">84 </sup>This was the dedication offering for the altar on the day when it was anointed, from the chiefs of Israel: twelve silver plates, twelve silver basins, twelve golden dishes,",
			"85": "<sup class=\"versenum\">85 </sup>each silver plate weighing 130 shekels and each basin 70, all the silver of the vessels 2,400 shekels according to the shekel of the sanctuary,",
			"86": "<sup class=\"versenum\">86 </sup>the twelve golden dishes, full of incense, weighing 10 shekels apiece according to the shekel of the sanctuary, all the gold of the dishes being 120 shekels;",
			"87": "<sup class=\"versenum\">87 </sup>all the cattle for the burnt offering twelve bulls, twelve rams, twelve male lambs a year old, with their grain offering; and twelve male goats for a sin offering;",
			"88": "<sup class=\"versenum\">88 </sup>and all the cattle for the sacrifice of peace offerings twenty-four bulls, the rams sixty, the male goats sixty, the male lambs a year old sixty. This was the dedication offering for the altar after it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3939AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3939AA\"></sup>was anointed.",
			"89": "<sup class=\"versenum\">89 </sup>And when Moses went into the tent of meeting <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3940AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3940AB\"></sup>to speak with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, he heard <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3940AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3940AC\"></sup>the voice speaking to him from above the mercy seat that was on the ark of the testimony, from between the two cherubim; and it spoke to him."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to Aaron and say to him, When you set up the lamps, the seven lamps shall give light in front of the lampstand.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And Aaron did so: he set up its lamps in front of the lampstand, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3944A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3944A\"></sup>this was the workmanship of the lampstand, hammered work of gold. From its base to its flowers, it was hammered work; according to the pattern that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had shown Moses, so he made the lampstand.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“Take the Levites from among the people of Israel and cleanse them.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Thus you shall do to them to cleanse them: sprinkle the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3947B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3947B\"></sup>water of purification upon them, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3947C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3947C\"></sup>let them go with a razor over all their body, and wash their clothes and cleanse themselves.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then let them take a bull from the herd and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3948D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3948D\"></sup>its grain offering of fine flour mixed with oil, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3948E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3948E\"></sup>and you shall take another bull from the herd for a sin offering.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3949F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3949F\"></sup>And you shall bring the Levites before the tent of meeting <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3949G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3949G\"></sup>and assemble the whole congregation of the people of Israel.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When you bring the Levites before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3950H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3950H\"></sup>shall lay their hands on the Levites,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and Aaron shall offer the Levites before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as a wave offering from the people of Israel, that they may do the service of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then the Levites <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3952I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3952I\"></sup>shall lay their hands on the heads of the bulls, and you shall offer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3952J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3952J\"></sup>the one for a sin offering and the other for a burnt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to make atonement for the Levites.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And you shall set the Levites before Aaron and his sons, and shall offer them as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3953K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3953K\"></sup>a wave offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“Thus you shall separate the Levites from among the people of Israel, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3954L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3954L\"></sup>the Levites shall be mine.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And after that the Levites shall go in to serve at the tent of meeting, when you have cleansed them and offered them as a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3955M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3955M\"></sup>wave offering.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>For they are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3956N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3956N\"></sup>wholly given to me from among the people of Israel. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3956O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3956O\"></sup>Instead of all who open the womb, the firstborn of all the people of Israel, I have taken them for myself.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3957P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3957P\"></sup>For all the firstborn among the people of Israel are mine, both of man and of beast. On the day that I struck down all the firstborn in the land of Egypt I consecrated them for myself,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and I have taken the Levites instead of all the firstborn among the people of Israel.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3959Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3959Q\"></sup>And I have given the Levites as a gift to Aaron and his sons from among the people of Israel, to do the service for the people of Israel at the tent of meeting and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3959R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3959R\"></sup>to make atonement for the people of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3959S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3959S\"></sup>that there may be no plague among the people of Israel when the people of Israel come near the sanctuary.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Thus did Moses and Aaron and all the congregation of the people of Israel to the Levites. According to all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses concerning the Levites, the people of Israel did to them.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3961T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3961T\"></sup>the Levites purified themselves from sin and washed their clothes, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3961U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3961U\"></sup>Aaron offered them as a wave offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and Aaron made atonement for them to cleanse them.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And after that the Levites went in to do their service in the tent of meeting before Aaron and his sons; as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses concerning the Levites, so they did to them.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“This applies to the Levites: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3964V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3964V\"></sup>from twenty-five years old and upward they shall come to do duty in the service of the tent of meeting.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And from the age of fifty years they shall withdraw from the duty of the service and serve no more.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>They minister to their brothers in the tent of meeting <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3966W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3966W\"></sup>by keeping guard, but they shall do no service. Thus shall you do to the Levites in assigning their duties.”"
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses in the wilderness of Sinai, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3967A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3967A\"></sup>in the first month of the second year after they had come out of the land of Egypt, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Let the people of Israel keep the Passover at its appointed time.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3969B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3969B\"></sup>On the fourteenth day of this month, at twilight, you shall keep it at its appointed time; according to all its statutes and all its rules you shall keep it.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Moses told the people of Israel that they should keep the Passover.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And they kept the Passover in the first month, on the fourteenth day of the month, at twilight, in the wilderness of Sinai; according to all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses, so the people of Israel did.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And there were certain men who were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3972C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3972C\"></sup>unclean through touching a dead body, so that they could not keep the Passover on that day, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3972D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3972D\"></sup>they came before Moses and Aaron on that day.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And those men said to him, “We are unclean through touching a dead body. Why are we kept from bringing the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3973E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3973E\"></sup>offering at its appointed time among the people of Israel?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And Moses said to them, “Wait, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3974F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3974F\"></sup>I may hear what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will command concerning you.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Speak to the people of Israel, saying, If any one of you or of your descendants is unclean through touching a dead body, or is on a long journey, he shall still keep the Passover to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3977G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3977G\"></sup>In the second month on the fourteenth day at twilight they shall keep it. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3977H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3977H\"></sup>They shall eat it with unleavened bread and bitter herbs.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3978I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3978I\"></sup>They shall leave none of it until the morning, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3978J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3978J\"></sup>nor break any of its bones; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3978K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3978K\"></sup>according to all the statute for the Passover they shall keep it.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But if anyone who is clean and is not on a journey fails to keep the Passover, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3979L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3979L\"></sup>that person shall be cut off from his people because he did not bring the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3979M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3979M\"></sup>offering at its appointed time; that man shall bear his sin.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And if a stranger sojourns among you and would keep the Passover to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, according to the statute of the Passover and according to its rule, so shall he do. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3980N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3980N\"></sup>You shall have one statute, both for the sojourner and for the native.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3981O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3981O\"></sup>On the day that the tabernacle was set up, the cloud covered the tabernacle, the tent of the testimony. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3981P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3981P\"></sup>at evening it was over the tabernacle like the appearance of fire until morning.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So it was always: the cloud covered it by day and the appearance of fire by night.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And whenever the cloud <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3983Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3983Q\"></sup>lifted from over the tent, after that the people of Israel set out, and in the place where the cloud settled down, there the people of Israel camped.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>At the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> the people of Israel set out, and at the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> they camped. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3984R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3984R\"></sup>As long as the cloud rested over the tabernacle, they remained in camp.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Even when the cloud continued over the tabernacle many days, the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3985S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3985S\"></sup>kept the charge of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and did not set out.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Sometimes the cloud was a few days over the tabernacle, and according to the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> they remained in camp; then according to the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> they set out.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And sometimes the cloud remained from evening until morning. And when the cloud lifted in the morning, they set out, or if it continued for a day and a night, when the cloud lifted they set out.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Whether it was two days, or a month, or a longer time, that the cloud continued over the tabernacle, abiding there, the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3988T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3988T\"></sup>remained in camp and did not set out, but when it lifted they set out.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>At the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> they camped, and at the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> they set out. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3989U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3989U\"></sup>They kept the charge of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, at the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by Moses."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Make two silver trumpets. Of hammered work you shall make them, and you shall use them for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3991A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3991A\"></sup>summoning the congregation and for breaking camp.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3992B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3992B\"></sup>both are blown, all the congregation shall gather themselves to you at the entrance of the tent of meeting.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But if they blow only one, then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3993C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3993C\"></sup>the chiefs, the heads of the tribes of Israel, shall gather themselves to you.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When you blow an alarm, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3994D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3994D\"></sup>the camps that are on the east side shall set out.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And when you blow an alarm the second time, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3995E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3995E\"></sup>the camps that are on the south side shall set out. An alarm is to be blown whenever they are to set out.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But when the assembly is to be gathered together, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3996F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3996F\"></sup>you shall blow a long blast, but you shall not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3996G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3996G\"></sup>sound an alarm.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3997H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3997H\"></sup>And the sons of Aaron, the priests, shall blow the trumpets. The trumpets shall be to you for a perpetual statute throughout your generations.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3998I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3998I\"></sup>when you go to war in your land against the adversary who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3998J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3998J\"></sup>oppresses you, then you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3998K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3998K\"></sup>sound an alarm with the trumpets, that you may be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3998L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3998L\"></sup>remembered before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and you shall be saved from your enemies.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3999M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3999M\"></sup>On the day of your gladness also, and at your appointed feasts and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3999N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3999N\"></sup>at the beginnings of your months, you shall blow the trumpets over your burnt offerings and over the sacrifices of your peace offerings. They shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3999O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3999O\"></sup>a reminder of you before your God: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>In the second year, in the second month, on the twentieth day of the month, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4000P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4000P\"></sup>the cloud lifted from over the tabernacle of the testimony,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4001Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4001Q\"></sup>set out by stages from the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4001R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4001R\"></sup>wilderness of Sinai. And the cloud settled down in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4001S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4001S\"></sup>wilderness of Paran.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>They set out for the first time <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4002T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4002T\"></sup>at the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by Moses.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The standard of the camp of the people of Judah set out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4003U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4003U\"></sup>first by their companies, and over their company was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4003V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4003V\"></sup>Nahshon the son of Amminadab.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And over the company of the tribe of the people of Issachar was Nethanel the son of Zuar.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And over the company of the tribe of the people of Zebulun was Eliab the son of Helon.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4006W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4006W\"></sup>the tabernacle was taken down, the sons of Gershon and the sons of Merari, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4006X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4006X\"></sup>who carried the tabernacle, set out.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4007Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4007Y\"></sup>the standard of the camp of Reuben set out by their companies, and over their company was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4007Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4007Z\"></sup>Elizur the son of Shedeur.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And over the company of the tribe of the people of Simeon was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4008AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4008AA\"></sup>Shelumiel the son of Zurishaddai.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And over the company of the tribe of the people of Gad was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4009AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4009AB\"></sup>Eliasaph the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4009AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4009AC\"></sup>Deuel.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then the Kohathites set out, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4010AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4010AD\"></sup>carrying the holy things, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4010AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4010AE\"></sup>the tabernacle was set up before their arrival.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4011AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4011AF\"></sup>the standard of the camp of the people of Ephraim set out by their companies, and over their company was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4011AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4011AG\"></sup>Elishama the son of Ammihud.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And over the company of the tribe of the people of Manasseh was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4012AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4012AH\"></sup>Gamaliel the son of Pedahzur.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And over the company of the tribe of the people of Benjamin was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4013AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4013AI\"></sup>Abidan the son of Gideoni.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4014AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4014AJ\"></sup>the standard of the camp of the people of Dan, acting as the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4014AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4014AK\"></sup>rear guard of all the camps, set out by their companies, and over their company was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4014AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4014AL\"></sup>Ahiezer the son of Ammishaddai.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And over the company of the tribe of the people of Asher was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4015AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4015AM\"></sup>Pagiel the son of Ochran.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And over the company of the tribe of the people of Naphtali was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4016AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4016AN\"></sup>Ahira the son of Enan.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4017AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4017AO\"></sup>This was the order of march of the people of Israel by their companies, when they set out.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And Moses said to Hobab the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4018AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4018AP\"></sup>Reuel the Midianite, Moses' father-in-law, “We are setting out for the place of which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4018AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4018AQ\"></sup>‘I will give it to you.’ Come with us, and we will do good to you, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4018AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4018AR\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has promised good to Israel.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But he said to him, “I will not go. I will depart to my own land and to my kindred.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And he said, “Please do not leave us, for you know where we should camp in the wilderness, and you will serve <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4020AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4020AS\"></sup>as eyes for us.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And if you do go with us, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4021AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4021AT\"></sup>whatever good the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will do to us, the same will we do to you.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>So they set out from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4022AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4022AU\"></sup>the mount of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> three days' journey. And the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> went before them three days' journey, to seek out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4022AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4022AV\"></sup>a resting place for them.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4023AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4023AW\"></sup>And the cloud of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was over them by day, whenever they set out from the camp.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And whenever the ark set out, Moses said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4024AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4024AX\"></sup>“Arise, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and let your enemies be scattered, and let those who hate you flee before you.”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And when it rested, he said, “Return, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, to the ten thousand thousands of Israel.”"
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4026A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4026A\"></sup>the people complained in the hearing of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> about their misfortunes, and when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> heard it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4026B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4026B\"></sup>his anger was kindled, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4026C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4026C\"></sup>the fire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> burned among them and consumed some outlying parts of the camp.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4027D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4027D\"></sup>the people cried out to Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4027E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4027E\"></sup>and Moses prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the fire died down.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So the name of that place was called <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4028F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4028F\"></sup>Taberah, because the fire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> burned among them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4029G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4029G\"></sup>rabble that was among them had a strong craving. And the people of Israel also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4029H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4029H\"></sup>wept again and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4029I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4029I\"></sup>“Oh that we had meat to eat!",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4030J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4030J\"></sup>We remember the fish we ate in Egypt that cost nothing, the cucumbers, the melons, the leeks, the onions, and the garlic.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But now our strength is dried up, and there is nothing at all but this manna to look at.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4032K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4032K\"></sup>the manna was like coriander seed, and its appearance like that of bdellium.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4033L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4033L\"></sup>The people went about and gathered it and ground it in handmills or beat it in mortars and boiled it in pots and made cakes of it. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4033M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4033M\"></sup>And the taste of it was like the taste of cakes baked with oil.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4034N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4034N\"></sup>When the dew fell upon the camp in the night, the manna fell with it.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Moses heard the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4035O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4035O\"></sup>weeping throughout their clans, everyone at the door of his tent. And the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> blazed hotly, and Moses was displeased.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4036P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4036P\"></sup>Moses said to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “Why have you dealt ill with your servant? And why have I not found favor in your sight, that you lay the burden of all this people on me?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Did I conceive all this people? Did I give them birth, that you should say to me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4037Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4037Q\"></sup>‘Carry them in your bosom, as a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4037R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4037R\"></sup>nurse carries a nursing child,’ to the land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4037S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4037S\"></sup>that you swore to give their fathers?",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4038T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4038T\"></sup>Where am I to get meat to give to all this people? For they weep before me and say, ‘Give us meat, that we may eat.’",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4039U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4039U\"></sup>I am not able to carry all this people alone; the burden is too heavy for me.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>If you will treat me like this, kill me at once, if I find favor in your sight, that I may not see my wretchedness.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Gather for me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4041V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4041V\"></sup>seventy men of the elders of Israel, whom you know to be the elders of the people and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4041W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4041W\"></sup>officers over them, and bring them to the tent of meeting, and let them take their stand there with you.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4042X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4042X\"></sup>And I will come down and talk with you there. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4042Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4042Y\"></sup>I will take some of the Spirit that is on you and put it on them, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4042Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4042Z\"></sup>they shall bear the burden of the people with you, so that you may not bear it yourself alone.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And say to the people, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4043AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4043AA\"></sup>‘Consecrate yourselves for tomorrow, and you shall eat meat, for you have wept in the hearing of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying, “Who will give us meat to eat? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4043AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4043AB\"></sup>For it was better for us in Egypt.” Therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will give you meat, and you shall eat.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>You shall not eat just one day, or two days, or five days, or ten days, or twenty days,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>but a whole month, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4045AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4045AC\"></sup>until it comes out at your nostrils and becomes loathsome to you, because you have rejected the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who is among you and have wept before him, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4045AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4045AD\"></sup>“Why did we come out of Egypt?”’”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But Moses said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4046AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4046AE\"></sup>“The people among whom I am number six hundred thousand on foot, and you have said, ‘I will give them meat, that they may eat a whole month!’",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4047AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4047AF\"></sup>Shall flocks and herds be slaughtered for them, and be enough for them? Or shall all the fish of the sea be gathered together for them, and be enough for them?”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4048AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4048AG\"></sup>“Is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s hand shortened? Now you shall see whether <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4048AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4048AH\"></sup>my word will come true for you or not.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So Moses went out and told the people the words of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4049AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4049AI\"></sup>And he gathered seventy men of the elders of the people and placed them around the tent.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4050AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4050AJ\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came down in the cloud and spoke to him, and took some of the Spirit that was on him and put it on the seventy elders. And as soon as the Spirit rested on them, they prophesied. But they did not continue doing it.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Now two men remained in the camp, one named Eldad, and the other named Medad, and the Spirit rested on them. They were among those registered, but they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4051AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4051AK\"></sup>had not gone out to the tent, and so they prophesied in the camp.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And a young man ran and told Moses, “Eldad and Medad are prophesying in the camp.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4053AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4053AL\"></sup>Joshua the son of Nun, the assistant of Moses from his youth, said, “My lord Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4053AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4053AM\"></sup>stop them.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>But Moses said to him, “Are you jealous for my sake? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4054AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4054AN\"></sup>Would that all the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s people were prophets, that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> would put his Spirit on them!”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And Moses and the elders of Israel returned to the camp.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4056AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4056AO\"></sup>wind from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sprang up, and it brought quail from the sea and let them fall beside the camp, about a day's journey on this side and a day's journey on the other side, around the camp, and about two cubits above the ground.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And the people rose all that day and all night and all the next day, and gathered the quail. Those who gathered least gathered ten <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4057AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4057AP\"></sup>homers. And they spread them out for themselves all around the camp.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4058AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4058AQ\"></sup>While the meat was yet between their teeth, before it was consumed, the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was kindled against the people, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4058AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4058AR\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> struck down the people with a very great plague.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Therefore the name of that place was called <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4059AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4059AS\"></sup>Kibroth-hattaavah, because there they buried the people who had the craving.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4060AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4060AT\"></sup>From Kibroth-hattaavah the people journeyed to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4060AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4060AU\"></sup>Hazeroth, and they remained at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4060AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4060AV\"></sup>Hazeroth."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>Miriam and Aaron spoke against Moses because of the Cushite woman whom he had married, for he had married a Cushite woman.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And they said, “Has the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> indeed spoken only through Moses? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4062A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4062A\"></sup>Has he not spoken through us also?” And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4062B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4062B\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> heard it.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now the man Moses was very meek, more than all people who were on the face of the earth.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And suddenly the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses and to Aaron and Miriam, “Come out, you three, to the tent of meeting.” And the three of them came out.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4065C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4065C\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came down in a pillar of cloud and stood at the entrance of the tent and called Aaron and Miriam, and they both came forward.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And he said, “Hear my words: If there is a prophet among you, I the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> make myself known to him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4066D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4066D\"></sup>in a vision; I speak with him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4066E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4066E\"></sup>in a dream.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Not so with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4067F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4067F\"></sup>my servant Moses. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4067G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4067G\"></sup>He is faithful in all my house.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>With him I speak <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4068H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4068H\"></sup>mouth to mouth, clearly, and not in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4068I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4068I\"></sup>riddles, and he beholds <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4068J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4068J\"></sup>the form of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Why then were you not afraid to speak against my servant Moses?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was kindled against them, and he departed.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When the cloud removed from over the tent, behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4070K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4070K\"></sup>Miriam was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4070L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4070L\"></sup>leprous, like snow. And Aaron turned toward Miriam, and behold, she was leprous.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And Aaron said to Moses, “Oh, my lord, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4071M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4071M\"></sup>do not punish us because we have done foolishly and have sinned.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Let her not be as one dead, whose flesh is half eaten away when he comes out of his mother's womb.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And Moses cried to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “O God, please heal her—please.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “If her father had but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4074N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4074N\"></sup>spit in her face, should she not be shamed seven days? Let her be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4074O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4074O\"></sup>shut outside the camp seven days, and after that she may be brought in again.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So Miriam <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4075P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4075P\"></sup>was shut outside the camp seven days, and the people did not set out on the march till Miriam was brought in again.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>After that the people set out from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4076Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4076Q\"></sup>Hazeroth, and camped in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4076R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4076R\"></sup>the wilderness of Paran."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4078A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4078A\"></sup>“Send men to spy out the land of Canaan, which I am giving to the people of Israel. From each tribe of their fathers you shall send a man, every one a chief among them.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So Moses sent them from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4079B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4079B\"></sup>the wilderness of Paran, according to the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, all of them men who were heads of the people of Israel.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And these were their names: From the tribe of Reuben, Shammua the son of Zaccur;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>from the tribe of Simeon, Shaphat the son of Hori;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4082C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4082C\"></sup>from the tribe of Judah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4082D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4082D\"></sup>Caleb the son of Jephunneh;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>from the tribe of Issachar, Igal the son of Joseph;",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>from the tribe of Ephraim, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4084E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4084E\"></sup>Hoshea the son of Nun;",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>from the tribe of Benjamin, Palti the son of Raphu;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>from the tribe of Zebulun, Gaddiel the son of Sodi;",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>from the tribe of Joseph (that is, from the tribe of Manasseh), Gaddi the son of Susi;",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>from the tribe of Dan, Ammiel the son of Gemalli;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>from the tribe of Asher, Sethur the son of Michael;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>from the tribe of Naphtali, Nahbi the son of Vophsi;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>from the tribe of Gad, Geuel the son of Machi.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>These were the names of the men whom Moses sent to spy out the land. And Moses called <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4092F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4092F\"></sup>Hoshea the son of Nun Joshua.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Moses sent them to spy out the land of Canaan and said to them, “Go up into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4093G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4093G\"></sup>the Negeb and go up into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4093H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4093H\"></sup>the hill country,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and see what the land is, and whether the people who dwell in it are strong or weak, whether they are few or many,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and whether the land that they dwell in is good or bad, and whether the cities that they dwell in are camps or strongholds,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and whether the land is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4096I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4096I\"></sup>rich or poor, and whether there are trees in it or not. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4096J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4096J\"></sup>Be of good courage and bring some of the fruit of the land.” Now the time was the season of the first ripe grapes.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So they went up and spied out the land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4097K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4097K\"></sup>from the wilderness of Zin to Rehob, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4097L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4097L\"></sup>near Lebo-hamath.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>They went up into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4098M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4098M\"></sup>the Negeb and came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4098N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4098N\"></sup>Hebron. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4098O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4098O\"></sup>Ahiman, Sheshai, and Talmai, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4098P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4098P\"></sup>descendants of Anak, were there. (<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4098Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4098Q\"></sup>Hebron was built seven years before <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4098R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4098R\"></sup>Zoan in Egypt.)",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4099S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4099S\"></sup>they came to the Valley of Eshcol and cut down from there a branch with a single cluster of grapes, and they carried it on a pole between two of them; they also brought some pomegranates and figs.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>That place was called the Valley of Eshcol, because of the cluster that the people of Israel cut down from there.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>At the end of forty days they returned from spying out the land.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And they came to Moses and Aaron and to all the congregation of the people of Israel in the wilderness of Paran, at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4102T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4102T\"></sup>Kadesh. They brought back word to them and to all the congregation, and showed them the fruit of the land.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And they told him, “We came to the land to which you sent us. It <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4103U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4103U\"></sup>flows with milk and honey, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4103V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4103V\"></sup>and this is its fruit.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4104W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4104W\"></sup>However, the people who dwell in the land are strong, and the cities are fortified and very large. And besides, we saw the descendants of Anak there.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4105X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4105X\"></sup>The Amalekites dwell in the land of the Negeb. The Hittites, the Jebusites, and the Amorites dwell in the hill country. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4105Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4105Y\"></sup>And the Canaanites dwell by the sea, and along the Jordan.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4106Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4106Z\"></sup>Caleb quieted the people before Moses and said, “Let us go up at once and occupy it, for we are well able to overcome it.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4107AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4107AA\"></sup>Then the men who had gone up with him said, “We are not able to go up against the people, for they are stronger than we are.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4108AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4108AB\"></sup>they brought to the people of Israel a bad report of the land that they had spied out, saying, “The land, through which we have gone to spy it out, is a land that devours its inhabitants, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4108AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4108AC\"></sup>all the people that we saw in it are of great height.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And there we saw the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4109AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4109AD\"></sup>Nephilim (the sons of Anak, who come from the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4109AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4109AE\"></sup>Nephilim), and we seemed to ourselves <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4109AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4109AF\"></sup>like grasshoppers, and so we seemed to them.”"
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>Then all the congregation raised a loud cry, and the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4110A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4110A\"></sup>wept that night.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And all the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4111B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4111B\"></sup>grumbled against Moses and Aaron. The whole congregation said to them, “Would that we had died in the land of Egypt! Or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4111C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4111C\"></sup>would that we had died in this wilderness!",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Why is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> bringing us into this land, to fall by the sword? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4112D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4112D\"></sup>Our wives and our little ones will become a prey. Would it not be better for us to go back to Egypt?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And they said to one another, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4113E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4113E\"></sup>“Let us choose a leader and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4113F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4113F\"></sup>go back to Egypt.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4114G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4114G\"></sup>Moses and Aaron fell on their faces before all the assembly of the congregation of the people of Israel.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4115H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4115H\"></sup>And Joshua the son of Nun and Caleb the son of Jephunneh, who were among those who had spied out the land, tore their clothes",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and said to all the congregation of the people of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4116I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4116I\"></sup>“The land, which we passed through to spy it out, is an exceedingly good land.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>If <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4117J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4117J\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> delights in us, he will bring us into this land and give it to us, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4117K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4117K\"></sup>a land that flows with milk and honey.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Only <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4118L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4118L\"></sup>do not rebel against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4118M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4118M\"></sup>do not fear the people of the land, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4118N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4118N\"></sup>they are bread for us. Their protection is removed from them, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is with us; do not fear them.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4119O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4119O\"></sup>Then all the congregation said to stone them with stones. But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4119P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4119P\"></sup>the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared at the tent of meeting to all the people of Israel.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “How long will this people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4120Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4120Q\"></sup>despise me? And how long will they not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4120R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4120R\"></sup>believe in me, in spite of all the signs that I have done among them?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>I will strike them with the pestilence and disinherit them, and I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4121S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4121S\"></sup>will make of you a nation greater and mightier than they.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4122T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4122T\"></sup>Moses said to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “Then the Egyptians will hear of it, for you brought up this people in your might from among them,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and they will tell the inhabitants of this land. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4123U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4123U\"></sup>They have heard that you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, are in the midst of this people. For you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, are seen face to face, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4123V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4123V\"></sup>your cloud stands over them and you go before them, in a pillar of cloud by day and in a pillar of fire by night.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now if you kill this people as one man, then the nations who have heard your fame will say,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>‘It is because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4125W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4125W\"></sup>was not able to bring this people into the land that he swore to give to them that he has killed them in the wilderness.’",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And now, please let the power of the Lord be great as you have promised, saying,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4127X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4127X\"></sup>‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is slow to anger and abounding in steadfast love, forgiving iniquity and transgression, but he will by no means clear the guilty, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4127Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4127Y\"></sup>visiting the iniquity of the fathers on the children, to the third and the fourth generation.’",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Please <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4128Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4128Z\"></sup>pardon the iniquity of this people, according to the greatness of your steadfast love, just <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4128AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4128AA\"></sup>as you have forgiven this people, from Egypt until now.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “I have pardoned, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4129AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4129AB\"></sup>according to your word.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But truly, as I live, and as all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4130AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4130AC\"></sup>the earth shall be filled with the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4131AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4131AD\"></sup>none of the men who have seen my glory and my signs that I did in Egypt and in the wilderness, and yet have put me to the test these <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4131AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4131AE\"></sup>ten times and have not obeyed my voice,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4132AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4132AF\"></sup>shall see the land that I swore to give to their fathers. And none of those who despised me shall see it.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But my servant <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4133AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4133AG\"></sup>Caleb, because he has a different spirit and has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4133AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4133AH\"></sup>followed me fully, I will bring into the land into which he went, and his descendants shall possess it.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4134AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4134AI\"></sup>Now, since the Amalekites and the Canaanites dwell in the valleys, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4134AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4134AJ\"></sup>turn tomorrow and set out for the wilderness by the way to the Red Sea.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses and to Aaron, saying,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“How long shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4136AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4136AK\"></sup>this wicked congregation grumble against me? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4136AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4136AL\"></sup>I have heard the grumblings of the people of Israel, which they grumble against me.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Say to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4137AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4137AM\"></sup>‘As I live, declares the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4137AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4137AN\"></sup>what you have said in my hearing I will do to you:",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4138AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4138AO\"></sup>your dead bodies shall fall in this wilderness, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4138AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4138AP\"></sup>of all your number, listed in the census <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4138AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4138AQ\"></sup>from twenty years old and upward, who have grumbled against me,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>not one shall come into the land where I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4139AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4139AR\"></sup>swore that I would make you dwell, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4139AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4139AS\"></sup>except Caleb the son of Jephunneh and Joshua the son of Nun.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4140AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4140AT\"></sup>But your little ones, who you said would become a prey, I will bring in, and they shall know the land that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4140AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4140AU\"></sup>you have rejected.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>But as for you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4141AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4141AV\"></sup>your dead bodies shall fall in this wilderness.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And your children <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4142AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4142AW\"></sup>shall be shepherds in the wilderness <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4142AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4142AX\"></sup>forty years and shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4142AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4142AY\"></sup>suffer for your faithlessness, until the last of your dead bodies lies in the wilderness.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4143AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4143AZ\"></sup>According to the number of the days in which you spied out the land, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4143BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4143BA\"></sup>forty days, a year for each day, you shall bear your iniquity forty years, and you shall know my displeasure.’",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4144BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4144BB\"></sup>I, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, have spoken. Surely this will I do to all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4144BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4144BC\"></sup>this wicked congregation who are gathered together against me: in this wilderness they shall come to a full end, and there they shall die.”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4145BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4145BD\"></sup>And the men whom Moses sent to spy out the land, who returned and made all the congregation grumble against him by bringing up a bad report about the land—",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>the men who brought up a bad report of the land—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4146BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4146BE\"></sup>died by plague before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Of those men who went to spy out the land, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4147BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4147BF\"></sup>only Joshua the son of Nun and Caleb the son of Jephunneh remained alive.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>When Moses told these words to all the people of Israel, the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4148BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4148BG\"></sup>mourned greatly.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>And they rose early in the morning and went up to the heights of the hill country, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4149BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4149BH\"></sup>“Here we are. We will go up to the place that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has promised, for we have sinned.”",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4150BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4150BI\"></sup>But Moses said, “Why now are you transgressing the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, when that will not succeed?",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4151BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4151BJ\"></sup>Do not go up, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4151BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4151BK\"></sup>for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is not among you, lest you be struck down before your enemies.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>For there <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4152BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4152BL\"></sup>the Amalekites and the Canaanites are facing you, and you shall fall by the sword. Because you have turned back from following the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will not be with you.”",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4153BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4153BM\"></sup>But they presumed to go up to the heights of the hill country, although neither <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4153BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4153BN\"></sup>the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> nor Moses departed out of the camp.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4154BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4154BO\"></sup>the Amalekites and the Canaanites who lived in that hill country came down and defeated them and pursued them, even to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4154BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4154BP\"></sup>Hormah."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to the people of Israel and say to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4156A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4156A\"></sup>When you come into the land you are to inhabit, which I am giving you,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4157B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4157B\"></sup>you offer to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> from the herd or from the flock a food offering or a burnt offering or a sacrifice, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4157C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4157C\"></sup>to fulfill a vow or as a freewill offering or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4157D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4157D\"></sup>at your appointed feasts, to make a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4157E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4157E\"></sup>pleasing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4158F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4158F\"></sup>he who brings his offering shall offer to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4158G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4158G\"></sup>a grain offering of a tenth of an ephah of fine flour, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4158H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4158H\"></sup>mixed with a quarter of a hin of oil;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and you shall offer with the burnt offering, or for the sacrifice, a quarter of a hin of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4159I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4159I\"></sup>wine for the drink offering for each lamb.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4160J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4160J\"></sup>Or for a ram, you shall offer for a grain offering two tenths of an ephah of fine flour mixed with a third of a hin of oil.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And for the drink offering you shall offer a third of a hin of wine, a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4161K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4161K\"></sup>pleasing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And when you offer a bull as a burnt offering or sacrifice, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4162L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4162L\"></sup>fulfill a vow or for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4162M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4162M\"></sup>peace offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>then one shall offer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4163N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4163N\"></sup>with the bull a grain offering of three tenths of an ephah of fine flour, mixed with half a hin of oil.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And you shall offer for the drink offering half a hin of wine, as a food offering, a pleasing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4165O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4165O\"></sup>“Thus it shall be done for each bull or ram, or for each lamb or young goat.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>As many as you offer, so shall you do with each one, as many as there are.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Every native Israelite shall do these things in this way, in offering a food offering, with a pleasing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And if a stranger is sojourning with you, or anyone is living permanently among you, and he wishes to offer a food offering, with a pleasing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, he shall do as you do.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>For the assembly, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4169P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4169P\"></sup>there shall be one statute for you and for the stranger who sojourns with you, a statute forever throughout your generations. You and the sojourner shall be alike before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>One law and one rule shall be for you and for the stranger who sojourns with you.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4172Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4172Q\"></sup>“Speak to the people of Israel and say to them, When you come into the land to which I bring you",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and when you eat of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4173R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4173R\"></sup>the bread of the land, you shall present a contribution to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4174S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4174S\"></sup>Of the first of your dough you shall present a loaf as a contribution; like a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4174T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4174T\"></sup>contribution from the threshing floor, so shall you present it.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4175U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4175U\"></sup>Some of the first of your dough you shall give to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as a contribution throughout your generations.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4176V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4176V\"></sup>“But if you sin unintentionally, and do not observe all these commandments that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has spoken to Moses,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded you by Moses, from the day that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave commandment, and onward throughout your generations,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>then if it was done unintentionally <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4178W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4178W\"></sup>without the knowledge of the congregation, all the congregation shall offer one bull from the herd for a burnt offering, a pleasing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4178X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4178X\"></sup>with its grain offering and its drink offering, according to the rule, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4178Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4178Y\"></sup>one male goat for a sin offering.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4179Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4179Z\"></sup>And the priest shall make atonement for all the congregation of the people of Israel, and they shall be forgiven, because it was a mistake, and they have brought their offering, a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and their sin offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for their mistake.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And all the congregation of the people of Israel shall be forgiven, and the stranger who sojourns among them, because the whole population was involved in the mistake.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4181AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4181AA\"></sup>“If one person sins unintentionally, he shall offer a female goat a year old for a sin offering.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4182AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4182AB\"></sup>And the priest shall make atonement before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for the person who makes a mistake, when he sins unintentionally, to make atonement for him, and he shall be forgiven.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4183AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4183AC\"></sup>You shall have one law for him who does anything unintentionally, for him who is native among the people of Israel and for the stranger who sojourns among them.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4184AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4184AD\"></sup>But the person who does anything with a high hand, whether he is native or a sojourner, reviles the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and that person shall be cut off from among his people.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Because he has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4185AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4185AE\"></sup>despised the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and has broken his commandment, that person shall be utterly cut off; his iniquity shall be on him.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>While the people of Israel were in the wilderness, they found a man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4186AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4186AF\"></sup>gathering sticks on the Sabbath day.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And those who found him gathering sticks brought him to Moses and Aaron and to all the congregation.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4188AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4188AG\"></sup>They put him in custody, because it had not been made clear what should be done to him.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4189AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4189AH\"></sup>“The man shall be put to death; all the congregation shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4189AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4189AI\"></sup>stone him with stones outside the camp.”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And all the congregation brought him outside the camp and stoned him to death with stones, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>“Speak to the people of Israel, and tell them to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4192AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4192AJ\"></sup>make tassels on the corners of their garments throughout their generations, and to put a cord of blue on the tassel of each corner.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>And it shall be a tassel for you to look at and remember all the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, to do them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4193AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4193AK\"></sup>not to follow after your own heart and your own eyes, which you are inclined <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4193AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4193AL\"></sup>to whore after.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>So you shall remember and do all my commandments, and be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4194AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4194AM\"></sup>holy to your God.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4195AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4195AN\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt to be your God: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.”"
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4196A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4196A\"></sup>Korah the son of Izhar, son of Kohath, son of Levi, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4196B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4196B\"></sup>Dathan and Abiram the sons of Eliab, and On the son of Peleth, sons of Reuben, took men.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And they rose up before Moses, with a number of the people of Israel, 250 chiefs of the congregation, chosen from the assembly, well-known men.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4198C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4198C\"></sup>They assembled themselves together against Moses and against Aaron and said to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4198D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4198D\"></sup>“You have gone too far! For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4198E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4198E\"></sup>all in the congregation are holy, every one of them, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is among them. Why then do you exalt yourselves above the assembly of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When Moses heard it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4199F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4199F\"></sup>he fell on his face,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and he said to Korah and all his company, “In the morning the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will show <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4200G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4200G\"></sup>who is his, and who is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4200H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4200H\"></sup>holy, and will bring him near to him. The one <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4200I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4200I\"></sup>whom he chooses he will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4200J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4200J\"></sup>bring near to him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Do this: take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4201K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4201K\"></sup>censers, Korah and all his company;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>put fire in them and put incense on them before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> tomorrow, and the man whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> chooses shall be the holy one. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4202L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4202L\"></sup>You have gone too far, sons of Levi!”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And Moses said to Korah, “Hear now, you sons of Levi:",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>is it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4204M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4204M\"></sup>too small a thing for you that the God of Israel has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4204N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4204N\"></sup>separated you from the congregation of Israel, to bring you near to himself, to do service in the tabernacle of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and to stand before the congregation to minister to them,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and that he has brought you near him, and all your brothers the sons of Levi with you? And would you seek the priesthood also?",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Therefore it is against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that you and all your company have gathered together. What is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4206O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4206O\"></sup>Aaron that you grumble against him?”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And Moses sent to call Dathan and Abiram the sons of Eliab, and they said, “We will not come up.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Is it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4208P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4208P\"></sup>a small thing that you have brought us up out of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4208Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4208Q\"></sup>a land flowing with milk and honey, to kill us in the wilderness, that you must also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4208R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4208R\"></sup>make yourself a prince over us?",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Moreover, you have not brought us into a land flowing with milk and honey, nor given us inheritance of fields and vineyards. Will you put out the eyes of these men? We will not come up.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And Moses was very angry and said to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4210S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4210S\"></sup>“Do not respect their offering. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4210T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4210T\"></sup>I have not taken one donkey from them, and I have not harmed one of them.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And Moses said to Korah, “Be present, you and all your company, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4211U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4211U\"></sup>before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you and they, and Aaron, tomorrow.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4212V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4212V\"></sup>let every one of you take his censer and put incense on it, and every one of you bring before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his censer, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4212W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4212W\"></sup>250 censers; you also, and Aaron, each his censer.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So every man took his censer and put fire in them and laid incense on them and stood at the entrance of the tent of meeting with Moses and Aaron.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then Korah assembled all the congregation against them at the entrance of the tent of meeting. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4214X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4214X\"></sup>And the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared to all the congregation.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses and to Aaron, saying,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4216Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4216Y\"></sup>“Separate yourselves from among this congregation, that I may consume them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4216Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4216Z\"></sup>in a moment.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4217AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4217AA\"></sup>fell on their faces and said, “O God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4217AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4217AB\"></sup>the God of the spirits of all flesh, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4217AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4217AC\"></sup>shall one man sin, and will you be angry with all the congregation?”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“Say to the congregation, Get away from the dwelling of Korah, Dathan, and Abiram.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then Moses rose and went to Dathan and Abiram, and the elders of Israel followed him.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And he spoke to the congregation, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4221AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4221AD\"></sup>“Depart, please, from the tents of these wicked men, and touch nothing of theirs, lest you be swept away with all their sins.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>So they got away from the dwelling of Korah, Dathan, and Abiram. And Dathan and Abiram came out and stood <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4222AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4222AE\"></sup>at the door of their tents, together with their wives, their sons, and their little ones.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And Moses said, “Hereby you shall know that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has sent me to do all these works, and that it has not been <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4223AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4223AF\"></sup>of my own accord.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>If these men die as all men die, or if they are visited by the fate of all mankind, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4224AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4224AG\"></sup>then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has not sent me.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But if the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> creates something new, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4225AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4225AH\"></sup>the ground opens its mouth and swallows them up with all that belongs to them, and they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4225AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4225AI\"></sup>go down alive into Sheol, then you shall know that these men have despised the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4226AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4226AJ\"></sup>And as soon as he had finished speaking all these words, the ground under them split apart.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And the earth opened its mouth and swallowed them up, with their households and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4227AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4227AK\"></sup>all the people who belonged to Korah and all their goods.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>So they and all that belonged to them went down alive into Sheol, and the earth closed over them, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4228AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4228AL\"></sup>they perished from the midst of the assembly.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And all Israel who were around them fled at their cry, for they said, “Lest the earth swallow us up!”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4230AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4230AM\"></sup>fire came out from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and consumed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4230AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4230AN\"></sup>the 250 men offering the incense.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup> Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>“Tell Eleazar the son of Aaron the priest to take up the censers out of the blaze. Then scatter the fire far and wide, for they have become holy.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>As for the censers of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4233AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4233AO\"></sup>these men who have sinned at the cost of their lives, let them be made into hammered plates as a covering for the altar, for they offered them before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and they became holy. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4233AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4233AP\"></sup>Thus they shall be a sign to the people of Israel.”",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>So Eleazar the priest took the bronze censers, which those who were burned had offered, and they were hammered out as a covering for the altar,",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>to be a reminder to the people of Israel, so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4235AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4235AQ\"></sup>that no outsider, who is not of the descendants of Aaron, should draw near to burn incense before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, lest he become like Korah and his company—as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him through Moses.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>But on the next day all the congregation of the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4236AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4236AR\"></sup>grumbled against Moses and against Aaron, saying, “You have killed the people of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>And when the congregation had assembled against Moses and against Aaron, they turned toward the tent of meeting. And behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4237AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4237AS\"></sup>the cloud covered it, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4237AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4237AT\"></sup>the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>And Moses and Aaron came to the front of the tent of meeting,",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4240AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4240AU\"></sup>“Get away from the midst of this congregation, that I may consume them in a moment.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4240AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4240AV\"></sup>And they fell on their faces.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>And Moses said to Aaron, “Take your censer, and put fire on it from off the altar and lay incense on it and carry it quickly to the congregation and make atonement for them, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4241AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4241AW\"></sup>wrath has gone out from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; the plague has begun.”",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>So Aaron took it as Moses said and ran into the midst of the assembly. And behold, the plague had already begun among the people. And he put on the incense and made atonement for the people.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>And he stood between the dead and the living, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4243AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4243AX\"></sup>the plague was stopped.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>Now those who died in the plague were 14,700, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4244AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4244AY\"></sup>besides those who died in the affair of Korah.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>And Aaron returned to Moses at the entrance of the tent of meeting, when the plague was stopped."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span> The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4247A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4247A\"></sup>“Speak to the people of Israel, and get from them staffs, one for each fathers' house, from all their chiefs according to their fathers' houses, twelve staffs. Write each man's name on his staff,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and write Aaron's name on the staff of Levi. For there shall be one staff for the head of each fathers' house.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then you shall deposit them in the tent of meeting before the testimony, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4249B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4249B\"></sup>where I meet with you.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the staff of the man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4250C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4250C\"></sup>whom I choose shall sprout. Thus I will make to cease from me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4250D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4250D\"></sup>the grumblings of the people of Israel, which they grumble against you.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Moses spoke to the people of Israel. And all their chiefs gave him staffs, one for each chief, according to their fathers' houses, twelve staffs. And the staff of Aaron was among their staffs.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And Moses deposited the staffs before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4252E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4252E\"></sup>the tent of the testimony.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>On the next day Moses went into the tent of the testimony, and behold, the staff of Aaron for the house of Levi had sprouted and put forth buds and produced blossoms, and it bore ripe almonds.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Moses brought out all the staffs from before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to all the people of Israel. And they looked, and each man took his staff.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Put back <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4255F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4255F\"></sup>the staff of Aaron before the testimony, to be kept <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4255G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4255G\"></sup>as a sign for the rebels, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4255H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4255H\"></sup>that you may make an end of their grumblings against me, lest they die.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Thus did Moses; as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded him, so he did.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And the people of Israel said to Moses, “Behold, we perish, we are undone, we are all undone.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4258I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4258I\"></sup>Everyone who comes near, who comes near to the tabernacle of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, shall die. Are we all to perish?”"
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Aaron, “You and your sons and your father's house with you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4259A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4259A\"></sup>bear iniquity connected with the sanctuary, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4259B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4259B\"></sup>and you and your sons with you shall bear iniquity connected with your priesthood.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And with you bring your brothers also, the tribe of Levi, the tribe of your father, that they may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4260C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4260C\"></sup>join you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4260D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4260D\"></sup>minister to you while you and your sons with you are before the tent of the testimony.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They shall keep guard over you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4261E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4261E\"></sup>over the whole tent, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4261F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4261F\"></sup>but shall not come near to the vessels of the sanctuary or to the altar <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4261G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4261G\"></sup>lest they, and you, die.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They shall join you and keep guard over the tent of meeting for all the service of the tent, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4262H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4262H\"></sup>and no outsider shall come near you.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4263I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4263I\"></sup>keep guard over the sanctuary and over the altar, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4263J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4263J\"></sup>that there may never again be wrath on the people of Israel.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4264K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4264K\"></sup>And behold, I have taken your brothers the Levites from among the people of Israel. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4264L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4264L\"></sup>They are a gift to you, given to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, to do the service of the tent of meeting.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4265M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4265M\"></sup>you and your sons with you shall guard your priesthood for all that concerns the altar and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4265N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4265N\"></sup>that is within the veil; and you shall serve. I give your priesthood as a gift, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4265O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4265O\"></sup>any outsider who comes near shall be put to death.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Aaron, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4266P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4266P\"></sup>I have given you charge of the contributions made to me, all the consecrated things of the people of Israel. I have given them to you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4266Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4266Q\"></sup>as a portion and to your sons as a perpetual due.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>This shall be yours of the most holy things, reserved from the fire: every offering of theirs, every grain offering of theirs and every <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4267R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4267R\"></sup>sin offering of theirs and every <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4267S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4267S\"></sup>guilt offering of theirs, which they render to me, shall be most holy to you and to your sons.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>In a most holy place shall you eat it. Every male may eat it; it is holy to you.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>This also is yours: the contribution of their gift, all the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4269T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4269T\"></sup>wave offerings of the people of Israel. I have given them to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4269U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4269U\"></sup>you, and to your sons and daughters with you, as a perpetual due. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4269V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4269V\"></sup>Everyone who is clean in your house may eat it.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4270W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4270W\"></sup>All the best of the oil and all the best of the wine and of the grain, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4270X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4270X\"></sup>the firstfruits of what they give to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, I give to you.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The first ripe fruits of all that is in their land, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4271Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4271Y\"></sup>which they bring to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, shall be yours. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4271Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4271Z\"></sup>Everyone who is clean in your house may eat it.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4272AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4272AA\"></sup>Every devoted thing in Israel shall be yours.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4273AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4273AB\"></sup>Everything that opens the womb of all flesh, whether man or beast, which they offer to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, shall be yours. Nevertheless, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4273AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4273AC\"></sup>the firstborn of man you shall redeem, and the firstborn of unclean animals you shall redeem.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And their redemption price <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4274AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4274AD\"></sup>(at a month old you shall redeem them) you shall fix at five shekels in silver, according to the shekel of the sanctuary, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4274AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4274AE\"></sup>which is twenty gerahs.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4275AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4275AF\"></sup>But the firstborn of a cow, or the firstborn of a sheep, or the firstborn of a goat, you shall not redeem; they are holy. You shall sprinkle their blood on the altar and shall burn their fat as a food offering, with a pleasing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But their flesh shall be yours, as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4276AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4276AG\"></sup>the breast that is waved and as the right thigh are yours.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4277AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4277AH\"></sup>All the holy contributions that the people of Israel present to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> I give to you, and to your sons and daughters with you, as a perpetual due. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4277AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4277AI\"></sup>It is a covenant of salt forever before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for you and for your offspring with you.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Aaron, “You shall have no inheritance in their land, neither shall you have any portion among them. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4278AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4278AJ\"></sup>I am your portion and your inheritance among the people of Israel.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4279AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4279AK\"></sup>“To the Levites I have given every tithe in Israel for an inheritance, in return for their service that they do, their service in the tent of meeting,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4280AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4280AL\"></sup>so that the people of Israel do not come near the tent of meeting, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4280AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4280AM\"></sup>lest they bear sin and die.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4281AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4281AN\"></sup>the Levites shall do the service of the tent of meeting, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4281AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4281AO\"></sup>and they shall bear their iniquity. It shall be a perpetual statute throughout your generations, and among the people of Israel they shall have no inheritance.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>For the tithe of the people of Israel, which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4282AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4282AP\"></sup>they present as a contribution to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, I have given to the Levites for an inheritance. Therefore I have said of them that they shall have no inheritance <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4282AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4282AQ\"></sup>among the people of Israel.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“Moreover, you shall speak and say to the Levites, ‘When you take from the people of Israel the tithe that I have given you from them for your inheritance, then you shall present a contribution from it to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4284AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4284AR\"></sup>a tithe of the tithe.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4285AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4285AS\"></sup>And your contribution shall be counted to you as though it were the grain of the threshing floor, and as the fullness of the winepress.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So you shall also present a contribution to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> from all your tithes, which you receive from the people of Israel. And from it you shall give the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s contribution to Aaron the priest.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Out of all the gifts to you, you shall present every contribution due to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; from each its best part is to be dedicated.’",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Therefore you shall say to them, ‘When you have offered from it the best of it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4288AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4288AT\"></sup>then the rest shall be counted to the Levites as produce of the threshing floor, and as produce of the winepress.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And you may eat it in any place, you and your households, for it is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4289AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4289AU\"></sup>your reward in return for your service in the tent of meeting.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4290AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4290AV\"></sup>bear no sin by reason of it, when you have contributed the best of it. But you shall not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4290AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4290AW\"></sup>profane the holy things of the people of Israel, lest you die.’”"
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses and to Aaron, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“This is the statute of the law that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded: Tell the people of Israel to bring you a red heifer without defect, in which there is no blemish, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4292A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4292A\"></sup>and on which a yoke has never come.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And you shall give it to Eleazar the priest, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4293B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4293B\"></sup>it shall be taken outside the camp and slaughtered before him.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And Eleazar the priest shall take some of its blood with his finger, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4294C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4294C\"></sup>sprinkle some of its blood toward the front of the tent of meeting seven times.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the heifer shall be burned in his sight. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4295D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4295D\"></sup>Its skin, its flesh, and its blood, with its dung, shall be burned.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And the priest shall take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4296E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4296E\"></sup>cedarwood and hyssop and scarlet yarn, and throw them into the fire burning the heifer.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then the priest <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4297F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4297F\"></sup>shall wash his clothes and bathe his body in water, and afterward he may come into the camp. But the priest shall be unclean until evening.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4298G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4298G\"></sup>The one who burns the heifer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4298H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4298H\"></sup>shall wash his clothes in water and bathe his body in water and shall be unclean until evening.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And a man who is clean shall gather up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4299I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4299I\"></sup>the ashes of the heifer and deposit them outside the camp in a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4299J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4299J\"></sup>clean place. And they shall be kept for the water for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4299K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4299K\"></sup>impurity for the congregation of the people of Israel; it is a sin offering.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And the one who gathers the ashes of the heifer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4300L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4300L\"></sup>shall wash his clothes and be unclean until evening. And this shall be a perpetual statute for the people of Israel, and for the stranger who sojourns among them.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4301M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4301M\"></sup>“Whoever touches the dead body of any person shall be unclean seven days.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4302N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4302N\"></sup>shall cleanse himself with the water on the third day and on the seventh day, and so be clean. But if he does not cleanse himself on the third day and on the seventh day, he will not become clean.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Whoever touches a dead person, the body of anyone who has died, and does not cleanse himself, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4303O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4303O\"></sup>defiles the tabernacle of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4303P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4303P\"></sup>and that person shall be cut off from Israel; because the water for impurity was not thrown on him, he shall be unclean. His uncleanness is still on him.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“This is the law when someone dies in a tent: everyone who comes into the tent and everyone who is in the tent shall be unclean seven days.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And every <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4305Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4305Q\"></sup>open vessel that has no cover fastened on it is unclean.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4306R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4306R\"></sup>Whoever in the open field touches someone who was killed with a sword or who died naturally, or touches a human bone or a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4306S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4306S\"></sup>grave, shall be unclean seven days.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>For the unclean they shall take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4307T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4307T\"></sup>some ashes of the burnt sin offering, and fresh water shall be added in a vessel.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then a clean person shall take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4308U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4308U\"></sup>hyssop and dip it in the water and sprinkle it on the tent and on all the furnishings and on the persons who were there and on whoever touched the bone, or the slain or the dead or the grave.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And the clean person shall sprinkle it on the unclean <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4309V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4309V\"></sup>on the third day and on the seventh day. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4309W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4309W\"></sup>Thus on the seventh day he shall cleanse him, and he shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4309X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4309X\"></sup>wash his clothes and bathe himself in water, and at evening he shall be clean.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“If the man who is unclean does not cleanse himself, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4310Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4310Y\"></sup>that person shall be cut off from the midst of the assembly, since he has defiled the sanctuary of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Because the water for impurity has not been thrown on him, he is unclean.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And it shall be a statute forever for them. The one who sprinkles the water for impurity shall wash his clothes, and the one who touches the water for impurity shall be unclean until evening.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4312Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4312Z\"></sup>whatever the unclean person touches shall be unclean, and anyone who touches it shall be unclean until evening.”"
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>And the people of Israel, the whole congregation, came <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4313A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4313A\"></sup>into the wilderness of Zin in the first month, and the people stayed in Kadesh. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4313B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4313B\"></sup>Miriam died there and was buried there.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4314C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4314C\"></sup>Now there was no water for the congregation. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4314D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4314D\"></sup>And they assembled themselves together against Moses and against Aaron.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4315E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4315E\"></sup>quarreled with Moses and said, “Would that we had perished <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4315F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4315F\"></sup>when our brothers perished before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Why have you brought the assembly of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> into this wilderness, that we should die here, both we and our cattle?",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4317G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4317G\"></sup>why have you made us come up out of Egypt to bring us to this evil place? It is no place for grain or figs or vines or pomegranates, and there is no water to drink.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Moses and Aaron went from the presence of the assembly to the entrance of the tent of meeting and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4318H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4318H\"></sup>fell on their faces. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4318I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4318I\"></sup>And the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared to them,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4320J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4320J\"></sup>“Take the staff, and assemble the congregation, you and Aaron your brother, and tell the rock before their eyes to yield its water. So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4320K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4320K\"></sup>you shall bring water out of the rock for them and give drink to the congregation and their cattle.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Moses took the staff <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4321L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4321L\"></sup>from before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as he commanded him.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Moses and Aaron gathered the assembly together before the rock, and he said to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4322M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4322M\"></sup>“Hear now, you rebels: shall we bring water for you out of this rock?”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And Moses lifted up his hand and struck the rock with his staff twice, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4323N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4323N\"></sup>and water came out abundantly, and the congregation drank, and their livestock.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses and Aaron, “Because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4324O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4324O\"></sup>you did not believe in me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4324P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4324P\"></sup>to uphold me as holy in the eyes of the people of Israel, therefore you shall not bring this assembly into the land that I have given them.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4325Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4325Q\"></sup>These are the waters of Meribah, where the people of Israel quarreled with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and through them he showed himself holy.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4326R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4326R\"></sup>Moses sent messengers from Kadesh to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4326S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4326S\"></sup>the king of Edom: “Thus says <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4326T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4326T\"></sup>your brother Israel: You know all the hardship that we have met:",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4327U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4327U\"></sup>how our fathers went down to Egypt, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4327V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4327V\"></sup>and we lived in Egypt a long time. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4327W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4327W\"></sup>And the Egyptians dealt harshly with us and our fathers.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4328X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4328X\"></sup>when we cried to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, he heard our voice and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4328Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4328Y\"></sup>sent an angel and brought us out of Egypt. And here we are in Kadesh, a city on the edge of your territory.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4329Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4329Z\"></sup>Please let us pass through your land. We will not pass through field or vineyard, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4329AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4329AA\"></sup>or drink water from a well. We will go along the King's Highway. We will not turn aside to the right hand or to the left until we have passed through your territory.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But Edom said to him, “You shall not pass through, lest I come out with the sword against you.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And the people of Israel said to him, “We will go up by the highway, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4331AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4331AB\"></sup>and if we drink of your water, I and my livestock, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4331AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4331AC\"></sup>then I will pay for it. Let me only pass through on foot, nothing more.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But he said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4332AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4332AD\"></sup>“You shall not pass through.” And Edom came out against them with a large army and with a strong force.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Thus Edom <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4333AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4333AE\"></sup>refused to give Israel passage through his territory, so Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4333AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4333AF\"></sup>turned away from him.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And they journeyed from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4334AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4334AG\"></sup>Kadesh, and the people of Israel, the whole congregation, came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4334AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4334AH\"></sup>Mount Hor.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses and Aaron at Mount Hor, on the border of the land of Edom,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4336AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4336AI\"></sup>“Let Aaron be gathered to his people, for he shall not enter the land that I have given to the people of Israel, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4336AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4336AJ\"></sup>you rebelled against my command at the waters of Meribah.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Take Aaron and Eleazar his son and bring them up to Mount Hor.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And strip Aaron of his garments and put them on Eleazar his son. And Aaron <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4338AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4338AK\"></sup>shall be gathered to his people and shall die there.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Moses did as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded. And they went up Mount Hor in the sight of all the congregation.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4340AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4340AL\"></sup>And Moses stripped Aaron of his garments and put them on Eleazar his son. And Aaron died there <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4340AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4340AM\"></sup>on the top of the mountain. Then Moses and Eleazar came down from the mountain.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And when all the congregation saw that Aaron had perished, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4341AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4341AN\"></sup>all the house of Israel wept for Aaron thirty days."
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4342A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4342A\"></sup>the Canaanite, the king of Arad, who lived in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4342B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4342B\"></sup>the Negeb, heard that Israel was coming by the way of Atharim, he fought against Israel, and took some of them captive.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4343C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4343C\"></sup>And Israel vowed a vow to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said, “If you will indeed give this people into my hand, then I will devote their cities to destruction.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> heeded the voice of Israel and gave over the Canaanites, and they devoted them and their cities to destruction. So the name of the place was called <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4344D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4344D\"></sup>Hormah.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>From Mount Hor <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4345E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4345E\"></sup>they set out by the way to the Red Sea, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4345F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4345F\"></sup>to go around the land of Edom. And the people became impatient on the way.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4346G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4346G\"></sup>spoke against God and against Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4346H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4346H\"></sup>“Why have you brought us up out of Egypt to die in the wilderness? For there is no food and no water, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4346I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4346I\"></sup>we loathe this worthless food.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4347J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4347J\"></sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent fiery serpents among the people, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4347K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4347K\"></sup>they bit the people, so that many people of Israel died.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4348L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4348L\"></sup>And the people came to Moses and said, “We have sinned, for we have spoken against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and against you. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4348M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4348M\"></sup>Pray to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, that he take away the serpents from us.” So Moses prayed for the people.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Make a fiery serpent and set it on a pole, and everyone who is bitten, when he sees it, shall live.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4350N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4350N\"></sup>Moses made a bronze serpent and set it on a pole. And if a serpent bit anyone, he would look at the bronze serpent and live.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And the people of Israel set out and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4351O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4351O\"></sup>camped in Oboth.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4352P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4352P\"></sup>And they set out from Oboth and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4352Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4352Q\"></sup>camped at Iye-abarim, in the wilderness that is opposite Moab, toward the sunrise.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>From there they set out and camped in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4353R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4353R\"></sup>the Valley of Zered.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>From there they set out and camped on the other side of the Arnon, which is in the wilderness that extends from the border of the Amorites, for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4354S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4354S\"></sup>Arnon is the border of Moab, between Moab and the Amorites.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Therefore it is said in the Book of the Wars of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,“Waheb in Suphah, and the valleys of the Arnon,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and the slope of the valleysthat extends to the seat of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4356T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4356T\"></sup>Ar,and leans to the border of Moab.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And from there they continued <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4357U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4357U\"></sup>to Beer; that is the well of which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Gather the people together, so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4357V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4357V\"></sup>I may give them water.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Israel sang this song:“Spring up, O well!—Sing to it!—",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>the well that the princes made,that the nobles of the people dug,with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4359W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4359W\"></sup>the scepter and with their staffs.”And from the wilderness they went on to Mattanah,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and from Mattanah to Nahaliel, and from Nahaliel to Bamoth,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and from Bamoth to the valley lying in the region of Moab by the top of Pisgah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4361X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4361X\"></sup>that looks down on the desert.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4362Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4362Y\"></sup>Israel sent messengers to Sihon king of the Amorites, saying,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4363Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4363Z\"></sup>“Let me pass through your land. We will not turn aside into field or vineyard. We will not drink the water of a well. We will go by the King's Highway until we have passed through your territory.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4364AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4364AA\"></sup>But Sihon would not allow Israel to pass through his territory. He gathered all his people together and went out against Israel to the wilderness and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4364AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4364AB\"></sup>came to Jahaz and fought against Israel.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4365AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4365AC\"></sup>And Israel defeated him with the edge of the sword and took possession of his land from the Arnon to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4365AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4365AD\"></sup>Jabbok, as far as to the Ammonites, for the border of the Ammonites was strong.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And Israel took all these cities, and Israel settled in all the cities of the Amorites, in Heshbon, and in all its villages.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>For Heshbon was the city of Sihon the king of the Amorites, who had fought against the former king of Moab and taken all his land out of his hand, as far as the Arnon.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Therefore the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4368AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4368AE\"></sup>ballad singers say,“Come to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4368AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4368AF\"></sup>Heshbon, let it be built;let the city of Sihon be established.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4369AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4369AG\"></sup>fire came out from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4369AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4369AH\"></sup>Heshbon,flame from the city of Sihon.It devoured <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4369AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4369AI\"></sup>Ar of Moab,and swallowed the heights of the Arnon.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4370AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4370AJ\"></sup>Woe to you, O Moab!You are undone, O people of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4370AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4370AK\"></sup>Chemosh!He has made his sons fugitives,and his daughters captives,to an Amorite king, Sihon.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>So we overthrew them;Heshbon, as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4371AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4371AL\"></sup>Dibon, perished;and we laid waste as far as Nophah;fire spread as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4371AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4371AM\"></sup>Medeba.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Thus Israel lived in the land of the Amorites.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And Moses sent to spy out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4373AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4373AN\"></sup>Jazer, and they captured its villages and dispossessed the Amorites who were there.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Then they turned and went up by the way to Bashan. And Og the king of Bashan came out against them, he and all his people, to battle <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4374AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4374AO\"></sup>at Edrei.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4375AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4375AP\"></sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Do not fear him, for I have given him into your hand, and all his people, and his land. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4375AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4375AQ\"></sup>you shall do to him as you did to Sihon king of the Amorites, who lived at Heshbon.”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>So they defeated him and his sons and all his people, until he had no survivor left. And they possessed his land."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4377A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4377A\"></sup>the people of Israel set out and camped in the plains of Moab beyond the Jordan at Jericho.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4378B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4378B\"></sup>Balak the son of Zippor saw all that Israel had done to the Amorites.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4379C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4379C\"></sup>Moab was in great dread of the people, because they were many. Moab was overcome with fear of the people of Israel.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And Moab said to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4380D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4380D\"></sup>the elders of Midian, “This horde will now lick up all that is around us, as the ox licks up the grass of the field.” So Balak the son of Zippor, who was king of Moab at that time,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4381E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4381E\"></sup>sent messengers to Balaam the son of Beor <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4381F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4381F\"></sup>at Pethor, which is near the River in the land of the people of Amaw, to call him, saying, “Behold, a people has come out of Egypt. They cover the face of the earth, and they are dwelling opposite me.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4382G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4382G\"></sup>Come now, curse this people for me, since they are too mighty for me. Perhaps I shall be able to defeat them and drive them from the land, for I know that he whom you bless is blessed, and he whom you curse is cursed.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So the elders of Moab and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4383H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4383H\"></sup>the elders of Midian departed with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4383I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4383I\"></sup>the fees for divination in their hand. And they came to Balaam and gave him Balak's message.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And he said to them, “Lodge here tonight, and I will bring back word to you, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> speaks to me.” So the princes of Moab stayed with Balaam.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4385J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4385J\"></sup>And God came to Balaam and said, “Who are these men with you?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And Balaam said to God, “Balak the son of Zippor, king of Moab, has sent to me, saying,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>‘Behold, a people has come out of Egypt, and it covers the face of the earth. Now come, curse them for me. Perhaps I shall be able to fight against them and drive them out.’”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>God said to Balaam, “You shall not go with them. You shall not curse the people, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4388K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4388K\"></sup>they are blessed.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So Balaam rose in the morning and said to the princes of Balak, “Go to your own land, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has refused to let me go with you.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So the princes of Moab rose and went to Balak and said, “Balaam refuses to come with us.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Once again Balak sent princes, more in number and more honorable than these.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And they came to Balaam and said to him, “Thus says Balak the son of Zippor: ‘Let nothing hinder you from coming to me,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4393L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4393L\"></sup>for I will surely do you great honor, and whatever you say to me I will do. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4393M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4393M\"></sup>Come, curse this people for me.’”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But Balaam answered and said to the servants of Balak, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4394N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4394N\"></sup>“Though Balak were to give me his house full of silver and gold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4394O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4394O\"></sup>I could not go beyond the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God to do less or more.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So you, too, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4395P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4395P\"></sup>please stay here tonight, that I may know what more the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will say to me.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4396Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4396Q\"></sup>And God came to Balaam at night and said to him, “If the men have come to call you, rise, go with them; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4396R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4396R\"></sup>but only do what I tell you.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So Balaam rose in the morning and saddled his donkey and went with the princes of Moab.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But God's anger was kindled because he went, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4398S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4398S\"></sup>and the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> took his stand in the way <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4398T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4398T\"></sup>as his adversary. Now he was riding on the donkey, and his two servants were with him.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And the donkey saw the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> standing in the road, with a drawn sword in his hand. And the donkey turned aside out of the road and went into the field. And Balaam struck the donkey, to turn her into the road.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> stood in a narrow path between the vineyards, with a wall on either side.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And when the donkey saw the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, she pushed against the wall and pressed Balaam's foot against the wall. So he struck her again.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> went ahead and stood in a narrow place, where there was no way to turn either to the right or to the left.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>When the donkey saw the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, she lay down under Balaam. And Balaam's anger was kindled, and he struck the donkey with his staff.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4404U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4404U\"></sup>opened the mouth of the donkey, and she said to Balaam, “What have I done to you, that you have struck me these three times?”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And Balaam said to the donkey, “Because you have made a fool of me. I wish I had a sword in my hand, for then I would kill you.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And the donkey said to Balaam, “Am I not your donkey, on which you have ridden all your life long to this day? Is it my habit to treat you this way?” And he said, “No.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4407V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4407V\"></sup>opened the eyes of Balaam, and he saw the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> standing in the way, with his drawn sword in his hand. And he bowed down and fell on his face.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “Why have you struck your donkey these three times? Behold, I have come out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4408W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4408W\"></sup>to oppose you because your way is perverse before me.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The donkey saw me and turned aside before me these three times. If she had not turned aside from me, surely just now I would have killed you and let her live.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then Balaam said to the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4410X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4410X\"></sup>“I have sinned, for I did not know that you stood in the road against me. Now therefore, if it is evil in your sight, I will turn back.”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Balaam, “Go with the men, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4411Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4411Y\"></sup>but speak only the word that I tell you.” So Balaam went on with the princes of Balak.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>When Balak heard that Balaam had come, he went out to meet him at the city of Moab, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4412Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4412Z\"></sup>on the border formed by the Arnon, at the extremity of the border.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And Balak said to Balaam, “Did I not send to you to call you? Why did you not come to me? Am I not able to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4413AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4413AA\"></sup>honor you?”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Balaam said to Balak, “Behold, I have come to you! Have I now any power of my own to speak anything? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4414AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4414AB\"></sup>The word that God puts in my mouth, that must I speak.”",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Then Balaam went with Balak, and they came to Kiriath-huzoth.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>And Balak sacrificed oxen and sheep, and sent for Balaam and for the princes who were with him.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>And in the morning Balak took Balaam and brought him up to Bamoth-baal, and from there he saw a fraction of the people."
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span>And Balaam said to Balak, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4418A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4418A\"></sup>“Build for me here seven altars, and prepare for me here seven bulls and seven rams.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Balak did as Balaam had said. And Balak and Balaam <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4419B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4419B\"></sup>offered on each altar a bull and a ram.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And Balaam said to Balak, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4420C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4420C\"></sup>“Stand beside your burnt offering, and I will go. Perhaps the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will come <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4420D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4420D\"></sup>to meet me, and whatever he shows me I will tell you.” And he went to a bare height,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4421E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4421E\"></sup>and God met Balaam. And Balaam said to him, “I have arranged the seven altars and I have offered on each altar a bull and a ram.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4422F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4422F\"></sup>put a word in Balaam's mouth and said, “Return to Balak, and thus you shall speak.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And he returned to him, and behold, he and all the princes of Moab were standing beside his burnt offering.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And Balaam <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4424G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4424G\"></sup>took up his discourse and said,“From <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4424H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4424H\"></sup>Aram Balak has brought me,the king of Moab <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4424I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4424I\"></sup>from the eastern mountains:‘Come, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4424J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4424J\"></sup>curse Jacob for me,and come, denounce Israel!’",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>How can I curse whom God has not cursed?How can I denounce whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has not denounced?",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For from the top of the crags <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4426K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4426K\"></sup>I see him,from the hills I behold him;behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4426L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4426L\"></sup>a people dwelling alone,and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4426M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4426M\"></sup>not counting itself among the nations!",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4427N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4427N\"></sup>Who can count the dust of Jacobor number the fourth part of Israel?Let me die <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4427O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4427O\"></sup>the death of the upright,and let my end be like his!”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And Balak said to Balaam, “What have you done to me? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4428P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4428P\"></sup>I took you to curse my enemies, and behold, you have done nothing but bless them.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And he answered and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4429Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4429Q\"></sup>“Must I not take care to speak what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> puts in my mouth?”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And Balak said to him, “Please come with me to another place, from which you may see them. You shall see only a fraction of them and shall not see them all. Then curse them for me from there.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And he took him to the field of Zophim, to the top of Pisgah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4431R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4431R\"></sup>and built seven altars and offered a bull and a ram on each altar.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Balaam said to Balak, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4432S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4432S\"></sup>“Stand here beside your burnt offering, while I meet the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> over there.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> met Balaam and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4433T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4433T\"></sup>put a word in his mouth and said, “Return to Balak, and thus shall you speak.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And he came to him, and behold, he was standing beside his burnt offering, and the princes of Moab with him. And Balak said to him, “What has the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoken?”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And Balaam took up his discourse and said,“Rise, Balak, and hear;give ear to me, O son of Zippor:",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4436U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4436U\"></sup>God is not man, that he should lie,or a son of man, that he should change his mind.Has he said, and will he not do it?Or has he spoken, and will he not fulfill it?",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Behold, I received a command to bless:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4437V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4437V\"></sup>he has blessed, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4437W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4437W\"></sup>I cannot revoke it.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4438X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4438X\"></sup>He has not beheld misfortune in Jacob,nor has he seen trouble in Israel.The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God is with them,and the shout of a king is among them.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4439Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4439Y\"></sup>God brings them out of Egyptand is for them like <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4439Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4439Z\"></sup>the horns of the wild ox.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>For there is no enchantment against Jacob,no <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4440AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4440AA\"></sup>divination against Israel;now it shall be said of Jacob and Israel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4440AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4440AB\"></sup>‘What has God wrought!’",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Behold, a people! <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4441AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4441AC\"></sup>As a lioness it rises upand as a lion it lifts itself;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4441AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4441AD\"></sup>it does not lie down until it has devoured the preyand drunk the blood of the slain.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And Balak said to Balaam, “Do not curse them at all, and do not bless them at all.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But Balaam answered Balak, “Did I not tell you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4443AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4443AE\"></sup>‘All that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says, that I must do’?”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And Balak said to Balaam, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4444AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4444AF\"></sup>“Come now, I will take you to another place. Perhaps it will please God that you may curse them for me from there.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So Balak took Balaam to the top of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4445AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4445AG\"></sup>Peor, which overlooks <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4445AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4445AH\"></sup>the desert.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And Balaam said to Balak, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4446AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4446AI\"></sup>“Build for me here seven altars and prepare for me here seven bulls and seven rams.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4447AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4447AJ\"></sup>And Balak did as Balaam had said, and offered a bull and a ram on each altar."
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span>When Balaam saw that it pleased the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to bless Israel, he did not go, as at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4448A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4448A\"></sup>other times, to look for omens, but set his face toward the wilderness.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Balaam lifted up his eyes and saw Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4449B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4449B\"></sup>camping tribe by tribe. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4449C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4449C\"></sup>the Spirit of God came upon him,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4450D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4450D\"></sup>took up his discourse and said,“The oracle of Balaam the son of Beor,the oracle of the man whose eye is opened,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>the oracle of him who hears the words of God,who sees the vision of the Almighty,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4451E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4451E\"></sup>falling down with his eyes uncovered:",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>How lovely are your tents, O Jacob,your encampments, O Israel!",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Like palm groves that stretch afar,like gardens beside a river,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4453F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4453F\"></sup>like aloes <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4453G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4453G\"></sup>that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has planted,like cedar trees beside the waters.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Water shall flow from his buckets,and his seed shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4454H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4454H\"></sup>in many waters;his king shall be higher than <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4454I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4454I\"></sup>Agag,and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4454J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4454J\"></sup>his kingdom shall be exalted.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>God brings him out of Egyptand is for him like the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4455K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4455K\"></sup>horns of the wild ox;he shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4455L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4455L\"></sup>eat up the nations, his adversaries,and shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4455M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4455M\"></sup>break their bones in piecesand <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4455N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4455N\"></sup>pierce them through with his arrows.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He crouched, he lay down like a lionand <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4456O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4456O\"></sup>like a lioness; who will rouse him up?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4456P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4456P\"></sup>Blessed are those who bless you,and cursed are those who curse you.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And Balak's anger was kindled against Balaam, and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4457Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4457Q\"></sup>struck his hands together. And Balak said to Balaam, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4457R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4457R\"></sup>“I called you to curse my enemies, and behold, you have blessed them these three times.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Therefore now flee to your own place. I said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4458S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4458S\"></sup>‘I will certainly honor you,’ but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has held you back from honor.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And Balaam said to Balak, “Did I not tell your messengers whom you sent to me,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4460T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4460T\"></sup>‘If Balak should give me his house full of silver and gold, I would not be able to go beyond the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, to do either good or bad <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4460U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4460U\"></sup>of my own will. What the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> speaks, that will I speak’?",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And now, behold, I am going to my people. Come, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4461V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4461V\"></sup>I will let you know what this people will do to your people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4461W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4461W\"></sup>in the latter days.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4462X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4462X\"></sup>And he took up his discourse and said,“The oracle of Balaam the son of Beor,the oracle of the man whose eye is opened,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>the oracle of him who hears the words of God,and knows the knowledge of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4463Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4463Y\"></sup>the Most High,who sees the vision of the Almighty,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4463Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4463Z\"></sup>falling down with his eyes uncovered:",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4464AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4464AA\"></sup>I see him, but not now;I behold him, but not near:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4464AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4464AB\"></sup>a star shall come out of Jacob,and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4464AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4464AC\"></sup>a scepter shall rise out of Israel;it shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4464AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4464AD\"></sup>crush the forehead of Moaband break down all the sons of Sheth.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4465AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4465AE\"></sup>Edom shall be dispossessed;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4465AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4465AF\"></sup>Seir also, his enemies, shall be dispossessed.Israel is doing valiantly.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And one from Jacob shall exercise dominionand destroy the survivors of cities!”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then he looked on Amalek and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4467AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4467AG\"></sup>took up his discourse and said,“Amalek was the first among the nations,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4467AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4467AH\"></sup>but its end is utter destruction.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And he looked on the Kenite, and took up his discourse and said,“Enduring is your dwelling place,and your nest is set in the rock.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Nevertheless, Kain shall be burnedwhen Asshur takes you away captive.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And he took up his discourse and said,“Alas, who shall live when God does this?",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>But ships shall come from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4471AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4471AI\"></sup>Kittimand shall afflict Asshur and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4471AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4471AJ\"></sup>Eber;and he too <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4471AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4471AK\"></sup>shall come to utter destruction.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then Balaam rose and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4472AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4472AL\"></sup>went back to his place. And Balak also went his way."
		},
		"25": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">25 </span>While Israel lived in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4473A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4473A\"></sup>Shittim, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4473B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4473B\"></sup>the people began to whore with the daughters of Moab.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4474C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4474C\"></sup>These invited the people to the sacrifices of their gods, and the people ate and bowed down to their gods.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So Israel yoked himself to Baal of Peor. And the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was kindled against Israel.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4476D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4476D\"></sup>“Take all the chiefs of the people and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4476E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4476E\"></sup>hang them in the sun before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4476F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4476F\"></sup>that the fierce anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> may turn away from Israel.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And Moses said to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4477G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4477G\"></sup>the judges of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4477H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4477H\"></sup>“Each of you kill those of his men who have yoked themselves to Baal of Peor.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And behold, one of the people of Israel came and brought a Midianite woman to his family, in the sight of Moses and in the sight of the whole congregation of the people of Israel, while they were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4478I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4478I\"></sup>weeping in the entrance of the tent of meeting.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4479J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4479J\"></sup>When Phinehas <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4479K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4479K\"></sup>the son of Eleazar, son of Aaron the priest, saw it, he rose and left the congregation and took a spear in his hand",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and went after the man of Israel into the chamber and pierced both of them, the man of Israel and the woman through her belly. Thus the plague on the people of Israel was stopped.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Nevertheless, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4481L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4481L\"></sup>those who died by the plague were twenty-four thousand.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“Phinehas the son of Eleazar, son of Aaron the priest, has turned back my wrath from the people of Israel, in that he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4483M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4483M\"></sup>was jealous with my jealousy among them, so that I did not consume the people of Israel in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4483N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4483N\"></sup>my jealousy.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Therefore say, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4484O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4484O\"></sup>‘Behold, I give to him my covenant of peace,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and it shall be to him and to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4485P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4485P\"></sup>his descendants after him the covenant of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4485Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4485Q\"></sup>a perpetual priesthood, because he was jealous for his God and made atonement for the people of Israel.’”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The name of the slain man of Israel, who was killed with the Midianite woman, was Zimri the son of Salu, chief of a father's house belonging to the Simeonites.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And the name of the Midianite woman who was killed was Cozbi the daughter of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4487R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4487R\"></sup>Zur, who was the tribal head of a father's house in Midian.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4489S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4489S\"></sup>“Harass the Midianites and strike them down,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>for they have harassed you with their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4490T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4490T\"></sup>wiles, with which they beguiled you in the matter of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4490U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4490U\"></sup>Peor, and in the matter of Cozbi, the daughter of the chief of Midian, their sister, who was killed on the day of the plague on account of Peor.”"
		},
		"26": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">26 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4491A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4491A\"></sup>After the plague, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses and to Eleazar the son of Aaron, the priest,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4492B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4492B\"></sup>“Take a census of all the congregation of the people of Israel, from twenty years old and upward, by their fathers' houses, all in Israel who are able to go to war.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And Moses and Eleazar the priest spoke with them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4493C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4493C\"></sup>in the plains of Moab by the Jordan at Jericho, saying,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“Take a census of the people, from twenty years old and upward,” as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4494D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4494D\"></sup>commanded Moses. The people of Israel who came out of the land of Egypt were:",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4495E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4495E\"></sup>Reuben, the firstborn of Israel; the sons of Reuben: of Hanoch, the clan of the Hanochites; of Pallu, the clan of the Palluites;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>of Hezron, the clan of the Hezronites; of Carmi, the clan of the Carmites.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>These are the clans of the Reubenites, and those listed were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4497F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4497F\"></sup>43,730.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And the sons of Pallu: Eliab.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The sons of Eliab: Nemuel, Dathan, and Abiram. These are the Dathan and Abiram, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4499G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4499G\"></sup>chosen from the congregation, who contended against Moses and Aaron in the company of Korah, when they contended against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4500H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4500H\"></sup>the earth opened its mouth and swallowed them up together with Korah, when that company died, when the fire devoured 250 men, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4500I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4500I\"></sup>they became a warning.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4501J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4501J\"></sup>the sons of Korah did not die.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4502K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4502K\"></sup>Simeon according to their clans: of Nemuel, the clan of the Nemuelites; of Jamin, the clan of the Jaminites; of Jachin, the clan of the Jachinites;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>of Zerah, the clan of the Zerahites; of Shaul, the clan of the Shaulites.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>These are the clans of the Simeonites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4504L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4504L\"></sup>22,200.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4505M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4505M\"></sup>Gad according to their clans: of Zephon, the clan of the Zephonites; of Haggi, the clan of the Haggites; of Shuni, the clan of the Shunites;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>of Ozni, the clan of the Oznites; of Eri, the clan of the Erites;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>of Arod, the clan of the Arodites; of Areli, the clan of the Arelites.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>These are the clans of the sons of Gad as they were listed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4508N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4508N\"></sup>40,500.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4509O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4509O\"></sup>Judah were Er and Onan; and Er and Onan died in the land of Canaan.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And the sons of Judah according to their clans were: of Shelah, the clan of the Shelanites; of Perez, the clan of the Perezites; of Zerah, the clan of the Zerahites.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And the sons of Perez were: of Hezron, the clan of the Hezronites; of Hamul, the clan of the Hamulites.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>These are the clans of Judah as they were listed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4512P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4512P\"></sup>76,500.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4513Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4513Q\"></sup>Issachar according to their clans: of Tola, the clan of the Tolaites; of Puvah, the clan of the Punites;",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>of Jashub, the clan of the Jashubites; of Shimron, the clan of the Shimronites.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>These are the clans of Issachar as they were listed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4515R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4515R\"></sup>64,300.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4516S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4516S\"></sup>Zebulun, according to their clans: of Sered, the clan of the Seredites; of Elon, the clan of the Elonites; of Jahleel, the clan of the Jahleelites.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>These are the clans of the Zebulunites as they were listed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4517T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4517T\"></sup>60,500.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4518U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4518U\"></sup>Joseph according to their clans: Manasseh and Ephraim.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4519V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4519V\"></sup>The sons of Manasseh: of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4519W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4519W\"></sup>Machir, the clan of the Machirites; and Machir was the father of Gilead; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4519X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4519X\"></sup>of Gilead, the clan of the Gileadites.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>These are the sons of Gilead: of Iezer, the clan of the Iezerites; of Helek, the clan of the Helekites;",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>and of Asriel, the clan of the Asrielites; and of Shechem, the clan of the Shechemites;",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>and of Shemida, the clan of the Shemidaites; and of Hepher, the clan of the Hepherites.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4523Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4523Y\"></sup>Zelophehad the son of Hepher had no sons, but daughters. And the names of the daughters of Zelophehad were Mahlah, Noah, Hoglah, Milcah, and Tirzah.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>These are the clans of Manasseh, and those listed were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4524Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4524Z\"></sup>52,700.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>These are the sons of Ephraim according to their clans: of Shuthelah, the clan of the Shuthelahites; of Becher, the clan of the Becherites; of Tahan, the clan of the Tahanites.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And these are the sons of Shuthelah: of Eran, the clan of the Eranites.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>These are the clans of the sons of Ephraim as they were listed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4527AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4527AA\"></sup>32,500. These are the sons of Joseph according to their clans.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4528AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4528AB\"></sup>Benjamin according to their clans: of Bela, the clan of the Belaites; of Ashbel, the clan of the Ashbelites; of Ahiram, the clan of the Ahiramites;",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>of Shephupham, the clan of the Shuphamites; of Hupham, the clan of the Huphamites.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>And the sons of Bela were Ard and Naaman: of Ard, the clan of the Ardites; of Naaman, the clan of the Naamites.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>These are the sons of Benjamin according to their clans, and those listed were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4531AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4531AC\"></sup>45,600.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>These are the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4532AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4532AD\"></sup>Dan according to their clans: of Shuham, the clan of the Shuhamites. These are the clans of Dan according to their clans.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>All the clans of the Shuhamites, as they were listed, were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4533AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4533AE\"></sup>64,400.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4534AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4534AF\"></sup>Asher according to their clans: of Imnah, the clan of the Imnites; of Ishvi, the clan of the Ishvites; of Beriah, the clan of the Beriites.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Of the sons of Beriah: of Heber, the clan of the Heberites; of Malchiel, the clan of the Malchielites.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>And the name of the daughter of Asher was Serah.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>These are the clans of the sons of Asher as they were listed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4537AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4537AG\"></sup>53,400.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4538AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4538AH\"></sup>Naphtali according to their clans: of Jahzeel, the clan of the Jahzeelites; of Guni, the clan of the Gunites;",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>of Jezer, the clan of the Jezerites; of Shillem, the clan of the Shillemites.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>These are the clans of Naphtali according to their clans, and those listed were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4540AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4540AI\"></sup>45,400.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>This was the list of the people of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4541AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4541AJ\"></sup>601,730.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4543AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4543AK\"></sup>“Among these the land shall be divided for inheritance according to the number of names.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4544AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4544AL\"></sup>To a large tribe you shall give a large inheritance, and to a small tribe you shall give a small inheritance; every tribe shall be given its inheritance in proportion to its list.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>But the land shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4545AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4545AM\"></sup>divided by lot. According to the names of the tribes of their fathers they shall inherit.",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>Their inheritance shall be divided according to lot between the larger and the smaller.”",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4547AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4547AN\"></sup>This was the list of the Levites according to their clans: of Gershon, the clan of the Gershonites; of Kohath, the clan of the Kohathites; of Merari, the clan of the Merarites.",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>These are the clans of Levi: the clan of the Libnites, the clan of the Hebronites, the clan of the Mahlites, the clan of the Mushites, the clan of the Korahites. And Kohath was the father of Amram.",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>The name of Amram's wife was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4549AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4549AO\"></sup>Jochebed the daughter of Levi, who was born to Levi in Egypt. And she bore to Amram Aaron and Moses and Miriam their sister.",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4550AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4550AP\"></sup>And to Aaron were born Nadab, Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar.",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4551AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4551AQ\"></sup>But Nadab and Abihu died when they offered unauthorized fire before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup>And those listed were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4552AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4552AR\"></sup>23,000, every male from a month old and upward. For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4552AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4552AS\"></sup>they were not listed among the people of Israel, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4552AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4552AT\"></sup>there was no inheritance given to them among the people of Israel.",
			"63": "<sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup>These were those listed by Moses and Eleazar the priest, who listed the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4553AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4553AU\"></sup>in the plains of Moab by the Jordan at Jericho.",
			"64": "<sup class=\"versenum\">64 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4554AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4554AV\"></sup>But among these there was not one of those listed by Moses and Aaron the priest, who had listed the people of Israel in the wilderness of Sinai.",
			"65": "<sup class=\"versenum\">65 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said of them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4555AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4555AW\"></sup>“They shall die in the wilderness.” Not one of them was left, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4555AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4555AX\"></sup>except Caleb the son of Jephunneh and Joshua the son of Nun."
		},
		"27": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">27 </span>Then drew near the daughters of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4556A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4556A\"></sup>Zelophehad the son of Hepher, son of Gilead, son of Machir, son of Manasseh, from the clans of Manasseh the son of Joseph. The names of his daughters were: Mahlah, Noah, Hoglah, Milcah, and Tirzah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And they stood before Moses and before Eleazar the priest and before the chiefs and all the congregation, at the entrance of the tent of meeting, saying,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“Our father <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4558B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4558B\"></sup>died in the wilderness. He was not among the company of those who gathered themselves together against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4558C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4558C\"></sup>in the company of Korah, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4558D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4558D\"></sup>died for his own sin. And he had no sons.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Why should the name of our father be taken away from his clan because he had no son? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4559E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4559E\"></sup>Give to us a possession among our father's brothers.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4560F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4560F\"></sup>brought their case before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“The daughters of Zelophehad <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4562G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4562G\"></sup>are right. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4562H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4562H\"></sup>You shall give them possession of an inheritance among their father's brothers and transfer the inheritance of their father to them.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And you shall speak to the people of Israel, saying, ‘If a man dies and has no son, then you shall transfer his inheritance to his daughter.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And if he has no daughter, then you shall give his inheritance to his brothers.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And if he has no brothers, then you shall give his inheritance to his father's brothers.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And if his father has no brothers, then you shall give his inheritance to the nearest <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4566I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4566I\"></sup>kinsman of his clan, and he shall possess it. And it shall be for the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4566J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4566J\"></sup>a statute and rule, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses.’”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Go up into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4567K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4567K\"></sup>this mountain of Abarim and see the land that I have given to the people of Israel.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When you have seen it, you also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4568L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4568L\"></sup>shall be gathered to your people, as your brother Aaron was,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4569M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4569M\"></sup>because you rebelled against my word in the wilderness of Zin when the congregation quarreled, failing <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4569N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4569N\"></sup>to uphold me as holy at the waters before their eyes.” (These are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4569O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4569O\"></sup>the waters of Meribah of Kadesh in the wilderness of Zin.)",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Moses spoke to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“Let the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4571P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4571P\"></sup>the God of the spirits of all flesh, appoint a man over the congregation",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4572Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4572Q\"></sup>shall go out before them and come in before them, who shall lead them out and bring them in, that the congregation of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> may not be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4572R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4572R\"></sup>as sheep that have no shepherd.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4573S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4573S\"></sup>Joshua the son of Nun, a man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4573T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4573T\"></sup>in whom is the Spirit, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4573U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4573U\"></sup>lay your hand on him.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Make him stand before Eleazar the priest and all the congregation, and you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4574V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4574V\"></sup>commission him in their sight.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>You shall invest him with some of your authority, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4575W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4575W\"></sup>that all the congregation of the people of Israel may obey.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And he shall stand before Eleazar the priest, who shall inquire for him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4576X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4576X\"></sup>by the judgment of the Urim before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. At his word they shall go out, and at his word they shall come in, both he and all the people of Israel with him, the whole congregation.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And Moses did as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded him. He took Joshua and made him stand before Eleazar the priest and the whole congregation,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>and he laid his hands on him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4578Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4578Y\"></sup>commissioned him as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> directed through Moses."
		},
		"28": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">28 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Command the people of Israel and say to them, ‘My offering, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4580A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4580A\"></sup>my food for my food offerings, my <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4580B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4580B\"></sup>pleasing aroma, you shall be careful to offer to me at its appointed time.’",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4581C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4581C\"></sup>And you shall say to them, This is the food offering that you shall offer to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: two male lambs a year old without blemish, day by day, as a regular offering.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The one lamb you shall offer in the morning, and the other lamb you shall offer at twilight;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4583D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4583D\"></sup>a tenth of an ephah of fine flour for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4583E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4583E\"></sup>a grain offering, mixed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4583F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4583F\"></sup>with a quarter of a hin of beaten oil.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>It is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4584G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4584G\"></sup>regular burnt offering, which was ordained at Mount Sinai for a pleasing aroma, a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Its drink offering shall be a quarter of a hin for each lamb. In the Holy Place you shall pour out a drink offering of strong drink to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The other lamb you shall offer at twilight. Like the grain offering of the morning, and like its drink offering, you shall offer it as a food offering, with a pleasing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“On the Sabbath day, two male lambs a year old without blemish, and two tenths of an ephah of fine flour for a grain offering, mixed with oil, and its drink offering:",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>this is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4588H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4588H\"></sup>the burnt offering of every Sabbath, besides the regular burnt offering and its drink offering.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4589I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4589I\"></sup>“At the beginnings of your months, you shall offer a burnt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: two bulls from the herd, one ram, seven male lambs a year old without blemish;",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4590J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4590J\"></sup>three tenths of an ephah of fine flour for a grain offering, mixed with oil, for each bull, and two tenths of fine flour for a grain offering, mixed with oil, for the one ram;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and a tenth of fine flour mixed with oil as a grain offering for every lamb; for a burnt offering with a pleasing aroma, a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Their drink offerings shall be half a hin of wine for a bull, a third of a hin for a ram, and a quarter of a hin for a lamb. This is the burnt offering of each month throughout the months of the year.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4593K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4593K\"></sup>one male goat for a sin offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; it shall be offered besides the regular burnt offering and its drink offering.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4594L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4594L\"></sup>“On the fourteenth day of the first month is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s Passover,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4595M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4595M\"></sup>and on the fifteenth day of this month is a feast. Seven days shall unleavened bread be eaten.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4596N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4596N\"></sup>On the first day there shall be a holy convocation. You shall not do any ordinary work,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>but offer a food offering, a burnt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: two bulls from the herd, one ram, and seven male lambs a year old; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4597O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4597O\"></sup>see that they are without blemish;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>also their grain offering of fine flour mixed with oil; three tenths of an ephah shall you offer for a bull, and two tenths for a ram;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>a tenth shall you offer for each of the seven lambs;",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4600P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4600P\"></sup>one male goat for a sin offering, to make atonement for you.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>You shall offer these besides the burnt offering of the morning, which is for a regular burnt offering.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>In the same way you shall offer daily, for seven days, the food of a food offering, with a pleasing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. It shall be offered besides the regular burnt offering and its drink offering.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4603Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4603Q\"></sup>on the seventh day you shall have a holy convocation. You shall not do any ordinary work.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“On <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4604R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4604R\"></sup>the day of the firstfruits, when you offer a grain offering of new grain to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at your Feast of Weeks, you shall have a holy convocation. You shall not do any ordinary work,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>but offer a burnt offering, with a pleasing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4605S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4605S\"></sup>two bulls from the herd, one ram, seven male lambs a year old;",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>also their grain offering of fine flour mixed with oil, three tenths of an ephah for each bull, two tenths for one ram,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>a tenth for each of the seven lambs;",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4608T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4608T\"></sup>one male goat, to make atonement for you.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Besides the regular burnt offering and its grain offering, you shall offer them and their drink offering. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4609U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4609U\"></sup>See that they are without blemish."
		},
		"29": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">29 </span>“On the first day of the seventh month you shall have a holy convocation. You shall not do any ordinary work. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4610A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4610A\"></sup>It is a day for you to blow the trumpets,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and you shall offer a burnt offering, for a pleasing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: one bull from the herd, one ram, seven male lambs a year old without blemish;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>also their grain offering of fine flour mixed with oil, three tenths of an ephah for the bull, two tenths for the ram,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and one tenth for each of the seven lambs;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4614B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4614B\"></sup>one male goat for a sin offering, to make atonement for you;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>besides <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4615C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4615C\"></sup>the burnt offering of the new moon, and its grain offering, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4615D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4615D\"></sup>the regular burnt offering and its grain offering, and their drink offering, according to the rule for them, for a pleasing aroma, a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4616E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4616E\"></sup>“On the tenth day of this seventh month you shall have a holy convocation and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4616F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4616F\"></sup>afflict yourselves. You shall do no work,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>but you shall offer a burnt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, a pleasing aroma: one bull from the herd, one ram, seven male lambs a year old: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4617G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4617G\"></sup>see that they are without blemish.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And their grain offering shall be of fine flour mixed with oil, three tenths of an ephah for the bull, two tenths for the one ram,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>a tenth for each of the seven lambs:",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4620H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4620H\"></sup>one male goat for a sin offering, besides <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4620I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4620I\"></sup>the sin offering of atonement, and the regular burnt offering and its grain offering, and their drink offerings.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4621J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4621J\"></sup>“On the fifteenth day of the seventh month you shall have a holy convocation. You shall not do any ordinary work, and you shall keep a feast to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> seven days.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4622K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4622K\"></sup>you shall offer a burnt offering, a food offering, with a pleasing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, thirteen bulls from the herd, two rams, fourteen male lambs a year old; they shall be without blemish;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and their grain offering of fine flour mixed with oil, three tenths of an ephah for each of the thirteen bulls, two tenths for each of the two rams,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and a tenth for each of the fourteen lambs;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>also one male goat for a sin offering, besides the regular burnt offering, its grain offering and its drink offering.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“On the second day twelve bulls from the herd, two rams, fourteen male lambs a year old without blemish,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>with the grain offering and the drink offerings for the bulls, for the rams, and for the lambs, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4627L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4627L\"></sup>in the prescribed quantities;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>also one male goat for a sin offering, besides the regular burnt offering and its grain offering, and their drink offerings.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“On the third day eleven bulls, two rams, fourteen male lambs a year old without blemish,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>with the grain offering and the drink offerings for the bulls, for the rams, and for the lambs, in the prescribed quantities;",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>also one male goat for a sin offering, besides the regular burnt offering and its grain offering and its drink offering.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“On the fourth day ten bulls, two rams, fourteen male lambs a year old without blemish,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>with the grain offering and the drink offerings for the bulls, for the rams, and for the lambs, in the prescribed quantities;",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>also one male goat for a sin offering, besides the regular burnt offering, its grain offering and its drink offering.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“On the fifth day nine bulls, two rams, fourteen male lambs a year old without blemish,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>with the grain offering and the drink offerings for the bulls, for the rams, and for the lambs, in the prescribed quantities;",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>also one male goat for a sin offering; besides the regular burnt offering and its grain offering and its drink offering.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“On the sixth day eight bulls, two rams, fourteen male lambs a year old without blemish,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>with the grain offering and the drink offerings for the bulls, for the rams, and for the lambs, in the prescribed quantities;",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>also one male goat for a sin offering; besides the regular burnt offering, its grain offering, and its drink offerings.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“On the seventh day seven bulls, two rams, fourteen male lambs a year old without blemish,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>with the grain offering and the drink offerings for the bulls, for the rams, and for the lambs, in the prescribed quantities;",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>also one male goat for a sin offering; besides the regular burnt offering, its grain offering, and its drink offering.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4644M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4644M\"></sup>“On the eighth day you shall have a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4644N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4644N\"></sup>solemn assembly. You shall not do any ordinary work,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>but you shall offer a burnt offering, a food offering, with a pleasing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: one bull, one ram, seven male lambs a year old without blemish,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>and the grain offering and the drink offerings for the bull, for the ram, and for the lambs, in the prescribed quantities;",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>also one male goat for a sin offering; besides the regular burnt offering and its grain offering and its drink offering.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>“These you shall offer to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4648O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4648O\"></sup>appointed feasts, in addition to your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4648P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4648P\"></sup>vow offerings and your freewill offerings, for your burnt offerings, and for your grain offerings, and for your drink offerings, and for your peace offerings.”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup> So Moses told the people of Israel everything just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses."
		},
		"30": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">30 </span>Moses spoke to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4650A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4650A\"></sup>the heads of the tribes of the people of Israel, saying, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4651B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4651B\"></sup>If a man vows a vow to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4651C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4651C\"></sup>swears an oath to bind himself by a pledge, he shall not break his word. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4651D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4651D\"></sup>He shall do according to all that proceeds out of his mouth.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“If a woman vows a vow to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and binds herself by a pledge, while within her father's house in her youth,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and her father hears of her vow and of her pledge by which she has bound herself and says nothing to her, then all her vows shall stand, and every pledge by which she has bound herself shall stand.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But if her father opposes her on the day that he hears of it, no vow of hers, no pledge by which she has bound herself shall stand. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will forgive her, because her father opposed her.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“If she marries a husband, while under her <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4655E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4655E\"></sup>vows or any thoughtless utterance of her lips by which she has bound herself,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and her husband hears of it and says nothing to her on the day that he hears, then her vows shall stand, and her pledges by which she has bound herself shall stand.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But if, on the day that her husband comes to hear of it, he opposes her, then he makes void her <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4657F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4657F\"></sup>vow that was on her, and the thoughtless utterance of her lips by which she bound herself. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4657G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4657G\"></sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will forgive her.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>(But any vow of a widow or of a divorced woman, anything by which she has bound herself, shall stand against her.)",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And if she vowed in her husband's house or bound herself by a pledge with an oath,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and her husband heard of it and said nothing to her and did not oppose her, then all her vows shall stand, and every pledge by which she bound herself shall stand.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But if her husband makes them null and void on the day that he hears them, then whatever proceeds out of her lips concerning her vows or concerning her pledge of herself shall not stand. Her husband has made them void, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4661H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4661H\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will forgive her.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Any vow and any binding oath to afflict herself, her husband may establish, or her husband may make void.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But if her husband says nothing to her from day to day, then he establishes all her vows or all her pledges that are upon her. He has established them, because he said nothing to her on the day that he heard of them.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But if he makes them null and void after he has heard of them, then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4664I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4664I\"></sup>he shall bear her iniquity.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>These are the statutes that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses about a man and his wife and about a father and his daughter while she is in her youth within her father's house."
		},
		"31": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">31 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4667A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4667A\"></sup>“Avenge the people of Israel on the Midianites. Afterward you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4667B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4667B\"></sup>be gathered to your people.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So Moses spoke to the people, saying, “Arm men from among you for the war, that they may go against Midian to execute the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s vengeance on Midian.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>You shall send a thousand from each of the tribes of Israel to the war.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So there were provided, out of the thousands of Israel, a thousand from each tribe, twelve thousand <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4670C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4670C\"></sup>armed for war.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And Moses sent them to the war, a thousand from each tribe, together with Phinehas the son of Eleazar the priest, with the vessels of the sanctuary and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4671D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4671D\"></sup>the trumpets for the alarm in his hand.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They warred against Midian, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4672E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4672E\"></sup>killed every male.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They killed the kings of Midian with the rest of their slain, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4673F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4673F\"></sup>Evi, Rekem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4673G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4673G\"></sup>Zur, Hur, and Reba, the five kings of Midian. And they also killed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4673H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4673H\"></sup>Balaam the son of Beor with the sword.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And the people of Israel took captive the women of Midian and their little ones, and they took as plunder all their cattle, their flocks, and all their goods.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>All their cities in the places where they lived, and all their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4675I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4675I\"></sup>encampments, they burned with fire,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4676J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4676J\"></sup>and took all the spoil and all the plunder, both of man and of beast.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then they brought the captives and the plunder and the spoil to Moses, and to Eleazar the priest, and to the congregation of the people of Israel, at the camp on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4677K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4677K\"></sup>the plains of Moab by the Jordan at Jericho.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Moses and Eleazar the priest and all the chiefs of the congregation went to meet them outside the camp.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And Moses was angry with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4679L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4679L\"></sup>the officers of the army, the commanders of thousands and the commanders of hundreds, who had come from service in the war.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Moses said to them, “Have you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4680M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4680M\"></sup>let all the women live?",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4681N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4681N\"></sup>these, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4681O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4681O\"></sup>on Balaam's advice, caused the people of Israel to act treacherously against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the incident of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4681P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4681P\"></sup>Peor, and so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4681Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4681Q\"></sup>the plague came among the congregation of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now therefore, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4682R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4682R\"></sup>kill every male among the little ones, and kill every woman who has known man by lying with him.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But all the young girls who have not known man by lying with him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4683S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4683S\"></sup>keep alive for yourselves.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4684T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4684T\"></sup>Encamp outside the camp seven days. Whoever of you has killed any person and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4684U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4684U\"></sup>whoever has touched any slain, purify yourselves and your captives on the third day and on the seventh day.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>You shall purify every garment, every article of skin, all work of goats' hair, and every article of wood.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Eleazar the priest said to the men in the army who had gone to battle: “This is the statute of the law that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded Moses:",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>only the gold, the silver, the bronze, the iron, the tin, and the lead,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>everything that can stand the fire, you shall pass through the fire, and it shall be clean. Nevertheless, it shall also be purified <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4688V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4688V\"></sup>with the water for impurity. And whatever cannot stand the fire, you shall pass through the water.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>You must <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4689W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4689W\"></sup>wash your clothes on the seventh day, and you shall be clean. And afterward you may come into the camp.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“Take the count of the plunder that was taken, both of man and of beast, you and Eleazar the priest and the heads of the fathers' houses of the congregation,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4692X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4692X\"></sup>divide the plunder into two parts between the warriors who went out to battle and all the congregation.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And levy for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> a tribute from the men of war who went out to battle, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4693Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4693Y\"></sup>one out of five hundred, of the people and of the oxen and of the donkeys and of the flocks.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Take it from their half and give it to Eleazar the priest as a contribution to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And from the people of Israel's half you shall take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4695Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4695Z\"></sup>one drawn out of every fifty, of the people, of the oxen, of the donkeys, and of the flocks, of all the cattle, and give them to the Levites <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4695AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4695AA\"></sup>who keep guard over the tabernacle of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And Moses and Eleazar the priest did as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Now the plunder remaining of the spoil that the army took was 675,000 sheep,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>72,000 cattle,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>61,000 donkeys,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>and 32,000 persons in all, women who had not known man by lying with him.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And the half, the portion of those who had gone out in the army, numbered 337,500 sheep,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4702AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4702AB\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s tribute of sheep was 675.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>The cattle were 36,000, of which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s tribute was 72.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>The donkeys were 30,500, of which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s tribute was 61.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>The persons were 16,000, of which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s tribute was 32 persons.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>And Moses gave the tribute, which was the contribution for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, to Eleazar the priest, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4706AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4706AC\"></sup>as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>From the people of Israel's half, which Moses separated from that of the men who had served in the army—",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>now the congregation's half was 337,500 sheep,",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>36,000 cattle,",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>and 30,500 donkeys,",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>and 16,000 persons—",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4712AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4712AD\"></sup>from the people of Israel's half Moses took one of every 50, both of persons and of beasts, and gave them to the Levites who kept guard over the tabernacle of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4713AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4713AE\"></sup>the officers who were over the thousands of the army, the commanders of thousands and the commanders of hundreds, came near to Moses",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>and said to Moses, “Your servants have counted the men of war who are under our command, and there is not a man missing from us.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>And we have brought the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s offering, what each man found, articles of gold, armlets and bracelets, signet rings, earrings, and beads, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4715AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4715AF\"></sup>to make atonement for ourselves before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>And Moses and Eleazar the priest received from them the gold, all crafted articles.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>And all the gold of the contribution that they presented to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, from the commanders of thousands and the commanders of hundreds, was 16,750 shekels.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4718AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4718AG\"></sup>(The men in the army had each taken plunder for himself.)",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>And Moses and Eleazar the priest received the gold from the commanders of thousands and of hundreds, and brought it into the tent of meeting, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4719AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4719AH\"></sup>as a memorial for the people of Israel before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"32": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">32 </span>Now the people of Reuben and the people of Gad had a very great number of livestock. And they saw the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4720A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4720A\"></sup>Jazer and the land of Gilead, and behold, the place was a place for livestock.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So the people of Gad and the people of Reuben came and said to Moses and to Eleazar the priest and to the chiefs of the congregation,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4722B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4722B\"></sup>“Ataroth, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4722C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4722C\"></sup>Dibon, Jazer, Nimrah, Heshbon, Elealeh, Sebam, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4722D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4722D\"></sup>Nebo, and Beon,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>the land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4723E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4723E\"></sup>that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> struck down before the congregation of Israel, is a land for livestock, and your servants have livestock.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And they said, “If we have found favor in your sight, let this land be given to your servants for a possession. Do not take us across the Jordan.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But Moses said to the people of Gad and to the people of Reuben, “Shall your brothers go to the war while you sit here?",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Why will you discourage the heart of the people of Israel from going over into the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given them?",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Your fathers did this, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4727F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4727F\"></sup>when I sent them from Kadesh-barnea to see the land.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For when they went up to the Valley of Eshcol and saw the land, they discouraged the heart of the people of Israel from going into the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had given them.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4729G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4729G\"></sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s anger was kindled on that day, and he swore, saying,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>‘Surely none of the men who came up out of Egypt, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4730H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4730H\"></sup>from twenty years old and upward, shall see the land that I swore to give <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4730I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4730I\"></sup>to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob, because they have not wholly followed me,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>none except Caleb the son of Jephunneh the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4731J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4731J\"></sup>Kenizzite and Joshua the son of Nun, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4731K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4731K\"></sup>they have wholly followed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s anger was kindled against Israel, and he made them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4732L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4732L\"></sup>wander in the wilderness forty years, until <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4732M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4732M\"></sup>all the generation that had done evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was gone.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And behold, you have risen in your fathers' place, a brood of sinful men, to increase still more the fierce anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> against Israel!",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>For if you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4734N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4734N\"></sup>turn away from following him, he will again abandon them in the wilderness, and you will destroy all this people.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then they came near to him and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4735O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4735O\"></sup>“We will build sheepfolds here for our livestock, and cities for our little ones,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4736P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4736P\"></sup>we will take up arms, ready to go before the people of Israel, until we have brought them to their place. And our little ones shall live in the fortified cities because of the inhabitants of the land.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4737Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4737Q\"></sup>We will not return to our homes until each of the people of Israel has gained his inheritance.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>For we will not inherit with them on the other side of the Jordan and beyond, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4738R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4738R\"></sup>because our inheritance has come to us on this side of the Jordan to the east.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4739S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4739S\"></sup>Moses said to them, “If you will do this, if you will take up arms to go before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for the war,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>and every armed man of you will pass over the Jordan before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, until he has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4740T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4740T\"></sup>driven out his enemies from before him",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>and the land is subdued before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; then after that you shall return and be free of obligation to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and to Israel, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4741U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4741U\"></sup>this land shall be your possession before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But if you will not do so, behold, you have sinned against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4742V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4742V\"></sup>be sure your sin will find you out.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4743W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4743W\"></sup>Build cities for your little ones and folds for your sheep, and do what you have promised.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And the people of Gad and the people of Reuben said to Moses, “Your servants will do as my lord commands.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4745X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4745X\"></sup>Our little ones, our wives, our livestock, and all our cattle shall remain there in the cities of Gilead,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4746Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4746Y\"></sup>but your servants will pass over, every man who is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4746Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4746Z\"></sup>armed for war, before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to battle, as my lord orders.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4747AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4747AA\"></sup>Moses gave command concerning them to Eleazar the priest and to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4747AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4747AB\"></sup>Joshua the son of Nun and to the heads of the fathers' houses of the tribes of the people of Israel.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And Moses said to them, “If the people of Gad and the people of Reuben, every man who is armed to battle before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, will pass with you over the Jordan and the land shall be subdued before you, then you shall give them the land of Gilead for a possession.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>However, if they will not pass over with you armed, they shall have possessions among you in the land of Canaan.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And the people of Gad and the people of Reuben answered, “What the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has said to your servants, we will do.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>We will pass over armed before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> into the land of Canaan, and the possession of our inheritance shall remain with us beyond the Jordan.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4752AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4752AC\"></sup>Moses gave to them, to the people of Gad and to the people of Reuben and to the half-tribe of Manasseh the son of Joseph, the kingdom of Sihon king of the Amorites and the kingdom of Og king of Bashan, the land and its cities with their territories, the cities of the land throughout the country.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And the people of Gad built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4753AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4753AD\"></sup>Dibon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4753AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4753AE\"></sup>Ataroth, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4753AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4753AF\"></sup>Aroer,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Atroth-shophan, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4754AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4754AG\"></sup>Jazer, Jogbehah,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4755AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4755AH\"></sup>Beth-nimrah and Beth-haran, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4755AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4755AI\"></sup>fortified cities, and folds for sheep.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And the people of Reuben built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4756AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4756AJ\"></sup>Heshbon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4756AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4756AK\"></sup>Elealeh, Kiriathaim,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4757AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4757AL\"></sup>Nebo, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4757AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4757AM\"></sup>Baal-meon (<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4757AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4757AN\"></sup>their names were changed), and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4757AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4757AO\"></sup>Sibmah. And they gave other names to the cities that they built.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>And the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4758AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4758AP\"></sup>Machir the son of Manasseh went to Gilead and captured it, and dispossessed the Amorites who were in it.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>And Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4759AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4759AQ\"></sup>gave Gilead to Machir the son of Manasseh, and he settled in it.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4760AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4760AR\"></sup>Jair the son of Manasseh went and captured their villages, and called them Havvoth-jair.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>And Nobah went and captured Kenath and its villages, and called it Nobah, after his own name."
		},
		"33": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">33 </span>These are the stages of the people of Israel, when they went out of the land of Egypt by their companies under the leadership of Moses and Aaron.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Moses wrote down their starting places, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4763A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4763A\"></sup>stage by stage, by command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and these are their stages according to their starting places.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4764B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4764B\"></sup>set out from Rameses in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4764C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4764C\"></sup>the first month, on the fifteenth day of the first month. On the day after the Passover, the people of Israel went out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4764D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4764D\"></sup>triumphantly in the sight of all the Egyptians,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>while the Egyptians were burying all their firstborn, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4765E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4765E\"></sup>whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had struck down among them. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4765F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4765F\"></sup>On their gods also the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> executed judgments.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So the people of Israel set out from Rameses and camped at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4766G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4766G\"></sup>Succoth.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And they set out from Succoth and camped at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4767H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4767H\"></sup>Etham, which is on the edge of the wilderness.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And they set out from Etham and turned back to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4768I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4768I\"></sup>Pi-hahiroth, which is east of Baal-zephon, and they camped before Migdol.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And they set out from before Hahiroth and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4769J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4769J\"></sup>passed through the midst of the sea into the wilderness, and they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4769K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4769K\"></sup>went a three days' journey in the wilderness of Etham and camped at Marah.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And they set out from Marah and came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4770L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4770L\"></sup>Elim; at Elim there were twelve springs of water and seventy palm trees, and they camped there.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And they set out from Elim and camped by the Red Sea.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And they set out from the Red Sea and camped in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4772M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4772M\"></sup>the wilderness of Sin.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And they set out from the wilderness of Sin and camped at Dophkah.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And they set out from Dophkah and camped at Alush.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And they set out from Alush and camped at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4775N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4775N\"></sup>Rephidim, where there was no water for the people to drink.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And they set out from Rephidim and camped in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4776O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4776O\"></sup>wilderness of Sinai.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And they set out from the wilderness of Sinai and camped at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4777P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4777P\"></sup>Kibroth-hattaavah.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And they set out from Kibroth-hattaavah and camped at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4778Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4778Q\"></sup>Hazeroth.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4779R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4779R\"></sup>set out from Hazeroth and camped at Rithmah.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And they set out from Rithmah and camped at Rimmon-perez.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And they set out from Rimmon-perez and camped at Libnah.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And they set out from Libnah and camped at Rissah.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And they set out from Rissah and camped at Kehelathah.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And they set out from Kehelathah and camped at Mount Shepher.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And they set out from Mount Shepher and camped at Haradah.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And they set out from Haradah and camped at Makheloth.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And they set out from Makheloth and camped at Tahath.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And they set out from Tahath and camped at Terah.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And they set out from Terah and camped at Mithkah.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And they set out from Mithkah and camped at Hashmonah.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And they set out from Hashmonah and camped at Moseroth.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And they set out from Moseroth and camped at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4792S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4792S\"></sup>Bene-jaakan.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And they set out from Bene-jaakan and camped at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4793T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4793T\"></sup>Hor-haggidgad.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And they set out from Hor-haggidgad and camped at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4794U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4794U\"></sup>Jotbathah.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And they set out from Jotbathah and camped at Abronah.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And they set out from Abronah and camped at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4796V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4796V\"></sup>Ezion-geber.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And they set out from Ezion-geber and camped in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4797W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4797W\"></sup>wilderness of Zin (that is, Kadesh).",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And they set out from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4798X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4798X\"></sup>Kadesh and camped at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4798Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4798Y\"></sup>Mount Hor, on the edge of the land of Edom.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>And Aaron the priest went up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4799Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4799Z\"></sup>Mount Hor at the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and died there, in the fortieth year after the people of Israel had come out of the land of Egypt, on the first day of the fifth month.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>And Aaron was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4800AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4800AA\"></sup>123 years old when he died on Mount Hor.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4801AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4801AB\"></sup>the Canaanite, the king of Arad, who lived in the Negeb in the land of Canaan, heard of the coming of the people of Israel.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>And they set out from Mount Hor and camped at Zalmonah.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>And they set out from Zalmonah and camped at Punon.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>And they set out from Punon and camped at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4804AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4804AC\"></sup>Oboth.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>And they set out from Oboth and camped at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4805AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4805AD\"></sup>Iye-abarim, in the territory of Moab.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>And they set out from Iyim and camped at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4806AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4806AE\"></sup>Dibon-gad.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>And they set out from Dibon-gad and camped at Almon-diblathaim.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>And they set out from Almon-diblathaim <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4808AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4808AF\"></sup>and camped in the mountains of Abarim, before Nebo.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>And they set out from the mountains of Abarim and camped in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4809AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4809AG\"></sup>the plains of Moab by the Jordan at Jericho;",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>they camped by the Jordan from Beth-jeshimoth as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4810AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4810AH\"></sup>Abel-shittim in the plains of Moab.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses in the plains of Moab by the Jordan at Jericho, saying,",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>“Speak to the people of Israel and say to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4812AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4812AI\"></sup>When you pass over the Jordan into the land of Canaan,",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4813AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4813AJ\"></sup>you shall drive out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4813AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4813AK\"></sup>all the inhabitants of the land from before you and destroy all their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4813AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4813AL\"></sup>figured stones and destroy all their metal images and demolish all their high places.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>And you shall take possession of the land and settle in it, for I have given the land to you to possess it.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4815AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4815AM\"></sup>You shall inherit the land by lot according to your clans. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4815AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4815AN\"></sup>To a large tribe you shall give a large inheritance, and to a small tribe you shall give a small inheritance. Wherever the lot falls for anyone, that shall be his. According to the tribes of your fathers you shall inherit.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>But if you do not drive out the inhabitants of the land from before you, then those of them whom you let remain shall be as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4816AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4816AO\"></sup>barbs in your eyes and thorns in your sides, and they shall trouble you in the land where you dwell.",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>And I will do to you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4817AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4817AP\"></sup>as I thought to do to them.”"
		},
		"34": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">34 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Command the people of Israel, and say to them, When you enter <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4819A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4819A\"></sup>the land of Canaan <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4819B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4819B\"></sup>(this is the land that shall fall to you for an inheritance, the land of Canaan as defined by its borders),",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4820C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4820C\"></sup>your south side shall be from the wilderness of Zin alongside Edom, and your southern border shall run from the end of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4820D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4820D\"></sup>the Salt Sea on the east.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And your border shall turn south of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4821E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4821E\"></sup>the ascent of Akrabbim, and cross to Zin, and its limit shall be south of Kadesh-barnea. Then it shall go on to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4821F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4821F\"></sup>Hazar-addar, and pass along to Azmon.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the border shall turn <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4822G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4822G\"></sup>from Azmon to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4822H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4822H\"></sup>the Brook of Egypt, and its limit shall be at the sea.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“For the western border, you shall have the Great Sea and its coast. This shall be your western border.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“This shall be your northern border: from the Great Sea you shall draw a line to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4824I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4824I\"></sup>Mount Hor.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>From Mount Hor you shall draw a line <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4825J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4825J\"></sup>to Lebo-hamath, and the limit of the border shall be at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4825K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4825K\"></sup>Zedad.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the border shall extend to Ziphron, and its limit shall be at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4826L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4826L\"></sup>Hazar-enan. This shall be your northern border.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“You shall draw a line for your eastern border from Hazar-enan to Shepham.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And the border shall go down from Shepham to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4828M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4828M\"></sup>Riblah on the east side of Ain. And the border shall go down and reach to the shoulder of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4828N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4828N\"></sup>the Sea of Chinnereth on the east.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And the border shall go down to the Jordan, and its limit shall be at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4829O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4829O\"></sup>the Salt Sea. This shall be your land as defined by its borders all around.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Moses commanded the people of Israel, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4830P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4830P\"></sup>“This is the land that you shall inherit by lot, which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded to give to the nine tribes and to the half-tribe.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4831Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4831Q\"></sup>For the tribe of the people of Reuben by fathers' houses and the tribe of the people of Gad by their fathers' houses have received their inheritance, and also the half-tribe of Manasseh.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The two tribes and the half-tribe have received their inheritance beyond the Jordan east of Jericho, toward the sunrise.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“These are the names of the men who shall divide the land to you for inheritance: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4834R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4834R\"></sup>Eleazar the priest and Joshua the son of Nun.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>You shall take one <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4835S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4835S\"></sup>chief from every tribe to divide the land for inheritance.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>These are the names of the men: Of the tribe of Judah, Caleb the son of Jephunneh.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Of the tribe of the people of Simeon, Shemuel the son of Ammihud.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Of the tribe of Benjamin, Elidad the son of Chislon.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Of the tribe of the people of Dan a chief, Bukki the son of Jogli.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Of the people of Joseph: of the tribe of the people of Manasseh a chief, Hanniel the son of Ephod.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And of the tribe of the people of Ephraim a chief, Kemuel the son of Shiphtan.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Of the tribe of the people of Zebulun a chief, Elizaphan the son of Parnach.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Of the tribe of the people of Issachar a chief, Paltiel the son of Azzan.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And of the tribe of the people of Asher a chief, Ahihud the son of Shelomi.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Of the tribe of the people of Naphtali a chief, Pedahel the son of Ammihud.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>These are the men whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded to divide the inheritance for the people of Israel in the land of Canaan."
		},
		"35": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">35 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4847A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4847A\"></sup>the plains of Moab by the Jordan at Jericho, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4848B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4848B\"></sup>“Command the people of Israel to give to the Levites some of the inheritance of their possession as cities for them to dwell in. And you shall give to the Levites pasturelands around the cities.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The cities shall be theirs to dwell in, and their pasturelands shall be for their cattle and for their livestock and for all their beasts.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The pasturelands of the cities, which you shall give to the Levites, shall reach from the wall of the city outward a thousand cubits all around.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And you shall measure, outside the city, on the east side two thousand cubits, and on the south side two thousand cubits, and on the west side two thousand cubits, and on the north side two thousand cubits, the city being in the middle. This shall belong to them as pastureland for their cities.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“The cities that you give to the Levites shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4852C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4852C\"></sup>the six cities of refuge, where you shall permit the manslayer to flee, and in addition to them you shall give forty-two cities.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>All the cities that you give to the Levites shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4853D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4853D\"></sup>forty-eight, with their pasturelands.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And as for the cities that you shall give <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4854E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4854E\"></sup>from the possession of the people of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4854F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4854F\"></sup>from the larger tribes you shall take many, and from the smaller tribes you shall take few; each, in proportion to the inheritance that it inherits, shall give of its cities to the Levites.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Speak to the people of Israel and say to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4856G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4856G\"></sup>When you cross the Jordan into the land of Canaan,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4857H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4857H\"></sup>then you shall select cities to be cities of refuge for you, that the manslayer who kills any person without intent may flee there.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The cities shall be for you a refuge from the avenger, that the manslayer may not die until he stands before the congregation for judgment.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And the cities that you give shall be your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4859I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4859I\"></sup>six cities of refuge.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4860J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4860J\"></sup>You shall give three cities beyond the Jordan, and three cities in the land of Canaan, to be cities of refuge.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>These six cities shall be for refuge for the people of Israel, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4861K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4861K\"></sup>for the stranger and for the sojourner among them, that anyone who kills any person without intent may flee there.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4862L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4862L\"></sup>“But if he struck him down with an iron object, so that he died, he is a murderer. The murderer shall be put to death.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And if he struck him down with a stone tool that could cause death, and he died, he is a murderer. The murderer shall be put to death.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Or if he struck him down with a wooden tool that could cause death, and he died, he is a murderer. The murderer shall be put to death.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4865M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4865M\"></sup>The avenger of blood shall himself put the murderer to death; when he meets him, he shall put him to death.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And if he pushed him out of hatred or hurled something at him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4866N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4866N\"></sup>lying in wait, so that he died,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>or in enmity struck him down with his hand, so that he died, then he who struck the blow shall be put to death. He is a murderer. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4867O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4867O\"></sup>The avenger of blood shall put the murderer to death when he meets him.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“But if he pushed him suddenly without enmity, or hurled anything on him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4868P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4868P\"></sup>without lying in wait",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>or used a stone that could cause death, and without seeing him dropped it on him, so that he died, though he was not his enemy and did not seek his harm,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4870Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4870Q\"></sup>the congregation shall judge between the manslayer and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4870R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4870R\"></sup>the avenger of blood, in accordance with these rules.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And the congregation shall rescue the manslayer from the hand of the avenger of blood, and the congregation shall restore him to his city of refuge to which he had fled, and he shall live in it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4871S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4871S\"></sup>until the death of the high priest <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4871T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4871T\"></sup>who was anointed with the holy oil.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But if the manslayer shall at any time go beyond the boundaries of his city of refuge to which he fled,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4873U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4873U\"></sup>the avenger of blood finds him outside the boundaries of his city of refuge, and the avenger of blood kills the manslayer, he shall not be guilty of blood.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>For he must remain in his city of refuge <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4874V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4874V\"></sup>until the death of the high priest, but after the death of the high priest the manslayer may return to the land of his possession.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And these things shall be for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4875W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4875W\"></sup>a statute and rule for you throughout your generations in all your dwelling places.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>“If anyone kills a person, the murderer shall be put to death on the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4876X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4876X\"></sup>evidence of witnesses. But no person shall be put to death on the testimony of one witness.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Moreover, you shall accept no ransom for the life of a murderer, who is guilty of death, but he shall be put to death.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And you shall accept no ransom for him who has fled to his city of refuge, that he may return to dwell in the land before the death of the high priest.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>You shall not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4879Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4879Y\"></sup>pollute the land in which you live, for blood <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4879Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4879Z\"></sup>pollutes the land, and no atonement can be made for the land for the blood that is shed in it, except <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4879AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4879AA\"></sup>by the blood of the one who shed it.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4880AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4880AB\"></sup>You shall not defile the land in which you live, in the midst of which I dwell, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4880AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4880AC\"></sup>for I the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> dwell in the midst of the people of Israel.”"
		},
		"36": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">36 </span>The heads of the fathers' houses of the clan of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4881A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4881A\"></sup>people of Gilead the son of Machir, son of Manasseh, from the clans of the people of Joseph, came near and spoke before Moses and before the chiefs, the heads of the fathers' houses of the people of Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>They said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4882B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4882B\"></sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded my lord to give the land for inheritance by lot to the people of Israel, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4882C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4882C\"></sup>my lord was commanded by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to give the inheritance of Zelophehad our brother to his daughters.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But if they are married to any of the sons of the other tribes of the people of Israel, then their inheritance will be taken from the inheritance of our fathers and added to the inheritance of the tribe into which they marry. So it will be taken away from the lot of our inheritance.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4884D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4884D\"></sup>the jubilee of the people of Israel comes, then their inheritance will be added to the inheritance of the tribe into which they marry, and their inheritance will be taken from the inheritance of the tribe of our fathers.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And Moses commanded the people of Israel according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying, “The tribe of the people of Joseph <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4885E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4885E\"></sup>is right.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commands concerning the daughters of Zelophehad: ‘Let them marry whom they think best, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4886F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4886F\"></sup>only they shall marry within the clan of the tribe of their father.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The inheritance of the people of Israel shall not be transferred from one tribe to another, for every one of the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4887G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4887G\"></sup>shall hold on to the inheritance of the tribe of his fathers.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4888H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4888H\"></sup>every daughter who possesses an inheritance in any tribe of the people of Israel shall be wife to one of the clan of the tribe of her father, so that every one of the people of Israel may possess the inheritance of his fathers.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So no inheritance shall be transferred from one tribe to another, for each of the tribes of the people of Israel shall hold on to its own inheritance.’”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The daughters of Zelophehad did as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4891I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4891I\"></sup>for Mahlah, Tirzah, Hoglah, Milcah, and Noah, the daughters of Zelophehad, were married to sons of their father's brothers.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They were married into the clans of the people of Manasseh the son of Joseph, and their inheritance remained in the tribe of their father's clan.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>These are the commandments and the rules that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded through Moses to the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4893J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4893J\"></sup>in the plains of Moab by the Jordan at Jericho."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;